WEBVTT

02:25.980 --> 02:27.606
Mr. Adams!

02:29.400 --> 02:30.735
Mr. Adams!

02:32.069 --> 02:33.404
Mr. Adams!

02:34.905 --> 02:36.240
There you are.

02:36.324 --> 02:39.118
Didn't you hear me call you, Mr. Adams?

02:39.201 --> 02:43.664
You could've shouted down something,
saved me climbing up four flights.

02:43.748 --> 02:47.293
A man that likes to talk
as much as you do, I'd think...

02:48.794 --> 02:52.048
What do you keep coming
up here for, Mr. Adams?

02:52.131 --> 02:54.925
Afraid someone's going to steal our bell?

02:55.593 --> 02:57.345
Well, don't worry.

02:57.428 --> 03:01.265
Been here more than 14 years,
and ain't been carried off once.

03:04.727 --> 03:07.855
Better get yourself
back down to congress, Mr. Adams.

03:07.938 --> 03:11.859
Getting ready to vote, and they said they
couldn't settle such an important question

03:11.942 --> 03:14.403
without Massachusetts being there.

03:15.905 --> 03:17.865
I can just imagine.

03:22.620 --> 03:27.208
All right. What burning issue
are we voting on this time?

03:27.291 --> 03:31.212
On whether or not
to Grant general Washington's request

03:31.295 --> 03:34.673
that all members
of the Rhode Island militia be required

03:34.757 --> 03:36.801
to wear matching uniforms.

03:38.260 --> 03:39.970
Oh, good god.

04:17.341 --> 04:19.093
I have come to the conclusion

04:19.176 --> 04:23.431
that one useless man is called a disgrace,

04:24.265 --> 04:27.726
that two are called a law firm,

04:28.185 --> 04:32.565
and that three or more become a congress.

04:32.648 --> 04:36.277
And, by god, I have had this congress.

04:36.360 --> 04:39.155
For 10 years,
king George and his parliament

04:39.238 --> 04:43.659
have gulled, cullied and diddled
these colonies with their illegal taxes.

04:43.742 --> 04:47.746
Stamp acts,
townshend acts, sugar acts, tea acts.

04:48.539 --> 04:50.541
And when we dared stand up like men,

04:50.624 --> 04:53.794
they have stopped our trade,
seized our ships,

04:53.878 --> 04:56.672
blockaded our ports, burned our towns,

04:56.755 --> 04:59.383
and spilled our blood.

04:59.467 --> 05:04.805
And still this congress refuses to Grant
any of my proposals on independence

05:04.889 --> 05:08.184
even so much as the courtesy
of open debate.

05:08.267 --> 05:11.312
Good god,
what in the hell are you waiting for?

05:12.146 --> 05:15.483
<i>Sit down, John. Sit down, John</i>

05:15.566 --> 05:17.318
Thomas, for god's sake, listen to me.

05:17.401 --> 05:19.111
<i>For god's sake, John, sit down</i>

05:19.195 --> 05:21.155
I've had enough of you, sir.

05:21.238 --> 05:22.781
<i>Sit down, John sit down, John</i>

05:22.865 --> 05:25.493
<i>for god's sake, John, sit down</i>

05:25.576 --> 05:27.161
<i>someone ought to open up a window</i>

05:27.244 --> 05:29.004
will you listen to me
and forget the window?

05:29.079 --> 05:30.247
<i>It's 90 degrees</i>

05:30.331 --> 05:32.124
<i>have mercy, John, please</i>

05:32.208 --> 05:34.502
<i>it's hot as hell in Philadelphia</i>

05:34.585 --> 05:37.087
<i>someone ought to open up a window</i>

05:37.171 --> 05:39.673
<i>I say vote yes</i>

05:39.757 --> 05:41.550
<i>vote yes</i>

05:41.634 --> 05:43.844
<i>vote for independency</i>

05:43.928 --> 05:46.514
<i>someone ought to open up a window</i>

05:46.597 --> 05:48.766
<i>I say vote yes</i>

05:48.849 --> 05:50.768
<i>sit down, John</i>

