13:11.667 --> 13:13.251
Franklin!

13:15.504 --> 13:16.797
Franklin!

13:18.674 --> 13:20.509
Where in hell are you?

13:21.802 --> 13:23.178
Franklin!

13:23.261 --> 13:25.681
I see you hiding behind that tree.

13:26.390 --> 13:27.724
It won't do you any good.

13:28.934 --> 13:31.770
Damn it, this is no time for playing games.

13:33.480 --> 13:36.817
Franklin, I have been looking
everywhere for you.

13:36.900 --> 13:39.194
Where in god's name have you been?

13:39.277 --> 13:42.239
Right here, John,
being preserved for posterity.

13:42.322 --> 13:43.865
Do you like it?

13:47.828 --> 13:49.246
It stinks.

13:49.329 --> 13:50.914
As ever, the soul of tact.

13:50.997 --> 13:52.499
Well, the man's no botticelli.

13:52.582 --> 13:54.459
And the subject's no Venus.

13:54.543 --> 13:57.421
Franklin, where were you last night
when I needed you?

13:57.504 --> 13:59.344
You should have heard
what I suffered in there.

13:59.381 --> 14:02.801
I heard, all right.
Along with the rest of Philadelphia.

14:02.884 --> 14:04.636
Lord, your voice is piercing, John.

14:04.720 --> 14:07.514
Well, I wish to heaven my arguments were.

14:08.056 --> 14:11.143
My god, Franklin,
when are they going to make up their minds?

14:11.226 --> 14:14.980
With one hand they can raise an army,
dispatch one of their own to lead it,

14:15.063 --> 14:17.315
and cheer the news from bunker's hill.

14:17.399 --> 14:20.152
And with the other,
they wave the olive branch,

14:20.235 --> 14:23.280
begging the king for a happy
and permanent reconciliation.

14:23.363 --> 14:25.949
Fat George has declared us in rebellion.

14:26.032 --> 14:27.617
Why in bloody hell can't they?

14:27.701 --> 14:31.246
John, really?
You talk as if independence were the rule.

14:31.329 --> 14:33.165
It's never been done before.

14:33.248 --> 14:36.208
No colony has ever broken from the
parent stem in the history of the world.

14:36.251 --> 14:39.337
Damn it, Franklin,
you make us sound treasonous.

14:39.421 --> 14:41.006
<i>Do i'.></i>

14:41.089 --> 14:42.466
treason, eh?

14:43.425 --> 14:47.846
Treason is a charge invented by winners
as an excuse for hanging the losers.

14:48.263 --> 14:51.308
I have more to do than stand here,
listening to you quote yourself.

14:51.433 --> 14:53.560
No, that was a new one.

14:53.643 --> 14:55.854
Damn it, Franklin, we're at war.

14:55.937 --> 14:57.856
To defend ourselves, nothing more.

14:57.939 --> 15:00.567
We expressed our displeasure,
the English moved against us,

15:00.650 --> 15:02.110
and we in turn have resisted.

15:02.194 --> 15:05.864
Now our fellow congressmen want to effect
a reconciliation before it becomes a war.

15:05.947 --> 15:07.616
Reconciliation, my ass.

15:07.699 --> 15:09.701
The people want independence.

15:09.785 --> 15:11.745
<i>The people have read
Mr. paine's common sense.</i>

15:11.828 --> 15:14.122
I doubt very much congress has.

15:14.581 --> 15:15.791
That's true.

15:15.874 --> 15:17.667
John, why don't you give it up?

15:17.751 --> 15:20.212
Nobody listens to you.
You're obnoxious and disliked.

15:21.630 --> 15:25.050
L'm not promoting John Adams.
I'm promoting independence.

15:25.133 --> 15:27.344
Evidently, they cannot help
connecting the two.

15:27.969 --> 15:29.805
Even your own cousin.

15:29.888 --> 15:33.141
And if Sam Adams can't put up with you,
nobody can.

15:33.683 --> 15:35.811
You're getting at something.

15:36.937 --> 15:38.772
How can you tell?

15:38.855 --> 15:40.124
All right, outwith it, Franklin.

15:40.148 --> 15:42.651
What new intrigue are you cooking up?

15:43.318 --> 15:46.154
Let someone else in congress propose.

15:47.030 --> 15:48.198
Never!

15:56.039 --> 15:58.333
Why? Who did you have in mind?

15:58.416 --> 16:00.627
I don't know.
I really haven't given it much thought.

16:03.171 --> 16:04.881
You sent for me, Benjamin?

16:05.715 --> 16:06.758
Never.

16:06.842 --> 16:10.011
- Hello, Johnny!
- Richard.

16:10.095 --> 16:12.514
Johnny and I need some advice.

16:13.014 --> 16:15.016
If it's mine to give, it's
yours, you know that.

16:15.100 --> 16:16.351
Thank you, Richard.

16:16.434 --> 16:19.938
As you know, the cause that we support
has come to a complete standstill.

16:20.021 --> 16:21.940
- Now why do you suppose that is?
- Simple.

16:22.023 --> 16:24.526
- Johnny here is obnoxious and disliked.
- That's true.

16:24.609 --> 16:27.112
Now, what's the solution, I wonder?

16:28.864 --> 16:31.366
Get somebody else in congress to propose.

16:31.449 --> 16:33.076
Richard, that's brilliant.

16:33.159 --> 16:35.078
- Wasn't that brilliant, John?
- Brilliant.

16:35.161 --> 16:37.372
Yes. Now the question remains,
who can it be?

16:37.455 --> 16:39.749
The man that we need
must belong to a delegation

16:39.833 --> 16:41.710
publicly committed
to support independence.

16:41.793 --> 16:43.521
And at the present time,
only Massachusetts,

16:43.545 --> 16:45.273
New Hampshire
and Delaware have declared our way.

16:45.297 --> 16:47.674
And Virginia. Don't forget Virginia, benjy.

16:47.757 --> 16:49.384
Richard, I haven't. How could I?

16:49.467 --> 16:52.637
But strictly speaking, while Virginia's
views on independence are well known,

16:52.721 --> 16:55.765
your legislature in williamsburg
has never formally authorized

16:55.849 --> 16:58.643
its delegation here in congress
to support the cause.

16:58.768 --> 17:02.439
Now, if we could think of a virginian
with enough influence to go down there

17:02.522 --> 17:04.148
and persuade the house of burgesses...

17:04.232 --> 17:07.234
Damn me if I haven't thought of someone!

17:07.319 --> 17:08.444
'Who?
'Who?

17:08.528 --> 17:09.529
Me.

17:09.613 --> 17:11.156
Why didn't I think of that?

17:11.239 --> 17:12.781
I'll leave tonight.

17:12.866 --> 17:15.410
Why, hell, I'll leave
right now, if you like.

17:15.618 --> 17:18.538
I'll just stop off in stratford long enough
to refresh the missus,

17:18.622 --> 17:21.040
and then straight to the matter.

17:21.124 --> 17:23.960
Yes, sir. I really have to compliment
you on yourjudgment, Johnny.

17:24.044 --> 17:25.462
Whoa, boy. Steady.

17:25.545 --> 17:28.381
You've come to the one colony
that can get the job done.

17:28.464 --> 17:31.676
Virginia, the land that gave
us our glorious commander in chief,

17:32.719 --> 17:33.887
George Washington,

17:33.970 --> 17:37.307
will now give the continent
its proposal on independence.

17:37.390 --> 17:40.560
And when Virginia proposes,
the south is bound to follow.

17:40.644 --> 17:44.064
And where the south goes,
the middle colonies go.

17:44.147 --> 17:46.149
Gentlemen, a salute.

17:46.232 --> 17:49.903
To Virginia,
the mother of American independence.

17:49.986 --> 17:53.281
Incredible. We're free,
and he hasn't even left yet.

17:53.365 --> 17:55.992
What makes you so sure you can do it?

17:57.160 --> 18:01.206
<i>My name is Richard Henry Lee
Virginia is my home</i>

