21:29.247 --> 21:33.168
<i>Forward, ho</i>

22:04.073 --> 22:06.743
- Excuse me.
- Yes?

22:06.826 --> 22:10.580
I'm Dr. lyman hall,
the new delegate from Georgia.

22:10.663 --> 22:14.042
I'm Andrew mcnair, congressional custodian.

22:14.125 --> 22:17.003
If you'll be wanting anything at all,
just holler out "mcnair"

22:17.086 --> 22:20.673
as all the others do
and there won't be too long to wait.

22:21.841 --> 22:23.927
Where does the Georgia delegation belong?

22:24.010 --> 22:28.097
They mill about over there in that corner,
near the two carolinas.

22:33.853 --> 22:36.022
It's after 10:00.

22:36.105 --> 22:38.149
I was told congress convenes at 10:00.

22:38.233 --> 22:42.362
Well, they'll be wandering in
any time now, sir, with old grape and guts

22:42.445 --> 22:44.280
- leading the pack.
- Old who?

22:44.364 --> 22:45.740
Mcnair!

22:45.823 --> 22:47.116
Grape and guts.

22:47.700 --> 22:48.868
'Nair!

22:49.994 --> 22:51.496
Fetch me a rum.

22:51.579 --> 22:55.667
Mr. Hopkins,
you'll be pleased to meet Dr. lyman hall.

22:57.043 --> 22:58.920
I don't need a doctor, damn it.

22:59.003 --> 23:01.256
New delegate from Georgia.

23:01.339 --> 23:03.466
Well, why didn't you say so?

23:04.217 --> 23:08.137
I'm Stephen Hopkins,
old delegate from Rhode Island.

23:08.221 --> 23:09.764
Mcnair, fetch two rums.

23:09.847 --> 23:12.475
I fear it's a little early in the day.

23:14.602 --> 23:16.187
Nonsense.

23:16.271 --> 23:20.733
It's a medicinal fact that rum
gets a man's heart started in the morning.

23:22.151 --> 23:24.529
I'm surprised you didn't know that.

23:24.612 --> 23:27.073
Speaking as the oldest man
in the congress, I can tell you...

23:27.156 --> 23:30.159
Ben Franklin is older by almost a year.

23:30.243 --> 23:31.452
Rum!

23:37.166 --> 23:38.501
Tell me, doctor.

23:38.584 --> 23:41.796
Where does Georgia stand
on the question of independence?

23:41.879 --> 23:44.173
With south Carolina, of course.

23:45.258 --> 23:46.968
Neddy, good morning.

23:47.051 --> 23:50.221
Neddy, come over here and shake the hand
of Dr. lyman hall of Georgia.

23:50.305 --> 23:53.266
Dr. hall, this here is
Edward Rutledge from...

23:53.349 --> 23:56.811
Whichever Carolina he says he's from.
God knows I can't keep them straight.

23:56.894 --> 23:59.272
- It's a pleasure, Dr. hall.
- Your servant, Mr. Rutledge.

23:59.355 --> 24:02.191
You've met the long
and the short of it now, doctor.

24:02.275 --> 24:04.986
Neddy here is just a lad.
He's the youngest of us.

24:05.069 --> 24:06.696
Except for Ben Franklin.

24:06.779 --> 24:09.073
- Mcnair!
- Your rum!

24:09.949 --> 24:12.577
Well, where did you go for it, man?
Jamaica?

24:13.453 --> 24:15.371
Well, now, come along, Dr. hall.

24:15.455 --> 24:19.500
I know you must be anxious
to meet your colleagues from the south.

24:21.169 --> 24:23.296
Doctor, may I present to you Joseph Hewes.

24:23.379 --> 24:26.049
This is Dr. lyman hall,
the new delegate from Georgia.

24:26.132 --> 24:27.532
An honor and a pleasure, gentlemen.

24:27.592 --> 24:29.469
Where do you stand on independence,
Dr. hall?

24:29.969 --> 24:32.138
I'm here without instructions, Mr. Hewes,

24:32.221 --> 24:35.016
able to vote my own personal convictions.

24:35.808 --> 24:37.268
And they are?

24:41.356 --> 24:42.607
Personal.

24:44.025 --> 24:45.651
Now, Dr. hall,

24:46.444 --> 24:48.780
the deep south speaks with one voice.

24:48.863 --> 24:50.239
It's traditional.

24:50.323 --> 24:53.493
Even more, it is historical.

24:54.410 --> 24:56.079
Enter Delaware.

24:58.247 --> 24:59.457
Speak plain, Rutledge.

24:59.540 --> 25:02.418
You know I can't follow a word
of your damn French.

25:02.502 --> 25:04.170
It's Latin, colonel mckean,

25:04.253 --> 25:08.007
a tribute to the eternal peace and Harmony
of the Delaware delegation.

25:08.091 --> 25:10.927
What are you saying, man?
You know perfectly well

25:11.010 --> 25:14.180
that neither Rodney nor i
can stand the sight of this louse.

25:14.263 --> 25:15.306
Now, Thomas...

25:15.390 --> 25:16.516
Gentlemen, please.

25:16.599 --> 25:19.727
This is Dr. lyman hall of Georgia.

25:20.686 --> 25:21.771
Caesar Rodney.

25:21.854 --> 25:22.897
- An honor, sir.
- Sir.

25:22.980 --> 25:26.526
George read and colonel Thomas mckean.

25:26.609 --> 25:27.729
- Dr. hall...
- Your servant.

25:27.985 --> 25:31.114
I wonder if I might speak
to you for a moment in private.

25:31.197 --> 25:32.365
By all means.

25:35.660 --> 25:36.661
Mcnair!

25:36.744 --> 25:38.287
I'm coming! I'm coming!

25:38.371 --> 25:40.706
Help me. I'm stuck.

25:43.751 --> 25:45.211
Tell me, sir,

25:45.753 --> 25:50.049
would you be a doctor
of medicine or theology?

25:50.758 --> 25:53.302
Both, Mr. Rodney.
Which one can be of service?

25:53.386 --> 25:55.972
By all means, the physician first.

25:56.055 --> 25:58.516
Then we shall see about the other.

25:59.642 --> 26:01.894
I shall call at your convenience, sir.

26:11.112 --> 26:15.700
I trust, Caesar, when you're through
converting the poor fellow to independency

26:15.783 --> 26:19.078
that you'll give
the opposition a fair crack at him.

26:20.121 --> 26:22.415
You're too late, John.

26:22.498 --> 26:24.959
Once I get them, they're got.

26:25.042 --> 26:30.006
Dr. lyman hall of Georgia,
Mr. John Dickinson of Pennsylvania.

26:30.089 --> 26:32.675
- An honor, sir.
- Your servant, sir.

26:32.758 --> 26:34.927
Tell me, doctor.

26:35.011 --> 26:36.804
Where do you stand on the question of...

26:37.096 --> 26:38.264
Independence?

26:38.764 --> 26:39.765
Treason.

26:42.727 --> 26:43.936
I've no stomach for it.

26:44.479 --> 26:47.064
Then be careful not to
dine with John Adams.

26:47.148 --> 26:48.691
Between the fish and the souffle,

26:48.774 --> 26:51.486
you'll find yourself
hanging from an English rope.

26:51.569 --> 26:52.778
Your servant, sir.

26:56.282 --> 27:00.578
Judge Wilson, forgive me,
but how can anyone see you

27:00.661 --> 27:04.624
if you insist on standing
in Mr. Dickinson's shadow?

27:05.833 --> 27:09.795
James Wilson, also of Pennsylvania.

27:09.879 --> 27:10.963
Sir.

27:12.340 --> 27:13.841
An honor, sir.

27:14.675 --> 27:16.802
Good morning. Good morning.

27:19.555 --> 27:21.682
Good morning, ladies. Good morning.

27:21.766 --> 27:23.309
Steady, steady.

27:24.936 --> 27:27.647
Make gangway, sir. Make gangway!

27:27.730 --> 27:29.982
Good morning, Mr. Wilson. Good morning.

27:30.066 --> 27:33.069
Watch where you're going, damn it.
Over there.

27:33.444 --> 27:36.405
Mcnair, get me out of this thing.

27:36.489 --> 27:38.616
Watch out for my foot.

27:38.699 --> 27:39.825
Good morning, all.

27:39.909 --> 27:41.869
- Morning, Ben.
- Morning, Ben.

27:42.203 --> 27:45.540
Here you are. Two coppers apiece.
Now, straight back to jail with you.

27:45.623 --> 27:48.209
- Good morning, Stephen.
- All right, Benjamin.

27:49.293 --> 27:50.545
Dear god.

27:53.256 --> 27:54.632
What are you staring at?

27:54.715 --> 27:56.926
Haven't you ever seen a great man before?

27:57.009 --> 27:59.303
Good lord, sir.
Do you have the honor to be Dr. Franklin?

27:59.387 --> 28:03.349
Yes, I have that honor. Unfortunately,
the gout accompanies the honor.

28:03.432 --> 28:04.952
Been living too high again, eh, pappy?

28:05.017 --> 28:08.938
Stephen, I only wish king George
felt like my big toe all over.

28:10.731 --> 28:14.485
Mcnair! Fetch a pillow and two more rums.

28:14.569 --> 28:16.004
Well, Franklin, where's that idiot Lee?

28:16.028 --> 28:17.655
Is he back yet? I don't see him.

28:17.738 --> 28:20.491
Softly, John. Your voice
is hurting my foot.

28:20.575 --> 28:24.161
One more Clay, Franklin. That's how long
I'll remain silent, not a minute longer.

28:24.245 --> 28:26.789
That strutting popinjay
was so damn sure of himself.

28:26.872 --> 28:29.083
He's had time to bring back
a dozen proposals by now.

28:29.166 --> 28:30.209
Tell me, James.

28:30.293 --> 28:33.629
How do you explain the strange,
monumental quietude

28:33.713 --> 28:36.215
that congress has been treated
to these past 30 days?

28:36.299 --> 28:39.927
Has the ill wind
of independence finally blown itself out?

28:40.803 --> 28:42.638
Well, if you ask me...

28:42.722 --> 28:46.392
For myself, I must confess
that a month free from new england noise

28:46.475 --> 28:48.436
is more therapeutic
than a month in the country.

28:48.519 --> 28:50.146
Don't you agree, James?

28:50.229 --> 28:51.355
Well, lfeel...

28:51.439 --> 28:53.482
Mr. Adams, pray look for your voice, sir.

28:53.566 --> 28:58.237
It cannot be far, and god knows we need
the entertainment in congress.

29:02.450 --> 29:03.659
Congratulations, John.

29:03.743 --> 29:05.762
You just made
your greatest contribution to independence.

29:05.786 --> 29:07.079
You kept your flap shut.

29:07.163 --> 29:08.581
One more day, Franklin.

29:08.664 --> 29:10.916
Then I shall do the proposing.

29:12.251 --> 29:15.963
Gentlemen, the usual morning
festivities concluded,

29:16.047 --> 29:18.466
I will now call congress to order.

29:18.883 --> 29:20.384
Mr. thomson.

29:23.971 --> 29:27.600
The second continental congress meeting in
the city of Philadelphia is now in session.

29:27.683 --> 29:31.228
7 June, 1776, the 380th meeting.

29:31.312 --> 29:32.938
Sweet Jesus!

29:34.774 --> 29:38.110
The honorable John hancock
of Massachusetts bay, president.

29:40.154 --> 29:43.032
Thank you, Mr. thomson. Mr. mcnair.

29:43.115 --> 29:46.452
The stores of rum and other
drinking spirits are hereby closed

29:46.535 --> 29:50.039
to the colony of Rhode Island
for a period of three days.

29:50.122 --> 29:51.499
Yes, sir.

29:51.582 --> 29:53.376
Johnny, you can't do that.

29:53.459 --> 29:56.754
Sit down, Mr. Hopkins.
You've abused the privilege.

29:59.256 --> 30:01.133
The chair would like to
take this opportunity

30:01.217 --> 30:04.178
to welcome Dr. lyman hall of Georgia
to this congress,

30:04.261 --> 30:06.263
and hopes he will make the best of it.

30:09.475 --> 30:11.352
My god, it's hot.

30:12.353 --> 30:14.563
The secretary will read the roll.

30:14.647 --> 30:16.899
All members present
with the following exceptions.

30:17.441 --> 30:20.236
"Mr. paine, Mr. Gerry,
Mr. Samuel Adams of Massachusetts,

30:20.319 --> 30:21.987
"Mr. Morton of Pennsylvania,

30:22.113 --> 30:24.323
"Mr. wythe and
Mr. Richard Henry Lee of Virginia."

30:24.824 --> 30:27.576
And the entire delegation of New Jersey.

30:27.993 --> 30:29.829
I'm concerned over the continual absence

30:29.912 --> 30:33.040
of one-thirteenth of this congress.
Where is New Jersey?

30:33.457 --> 30:36.335
Somewhere between
New York and Pennsylvania.

30:39.839 --> 30:41.590
Thank you very much.

30:42.341 --> 30:46.137
Dr. Franklin, have you heard anything?
Your son resides there.

30:46.220 --> 30:47.471
Son, sir? What son?

30:48.431 --> 30:51.058
The royal governor of New Jersey, sir.

30:51.767 --> 30:53.769
As that title might suggest, sir,

30:53.853 --> 30:56.188
we are not in touch at the present time.

30:56.605 --> 30:58.441
Yes. Well...

30:59.024 --> 31:00.943
Now for the weather report,

31:01.026 --> 31:03.028
Mr. Jefferson of Virginia.

31:05.322 --> 31:06.323
Mr. Jefferson!

31:07.408 --> 31:08.534
Present, sir.

31:09.076 --> 31:10.703
May we hear about the weather?

31:10.995 --> 31:13.581
As if it weren't speaking for itself.

31:15.207 --> 31:17.793
Eighty-seven degrees of temperature,

31:17.877 --> 31:20.880
thirty-point-aught-six inches of Mercury.

31:21.505 --> 31:22.715
Wind...

31:23.758 --> 31:26.093
From the southwest for the rest of the day.

31:26.177 --> 31:27.636
And tonight...

31:27.720 --> 31:29.972
Tonight I'm leaving for home.

31:30.055 --> 31:31.515
On business?

31:31.599 --> 31:32.683
Family business.

31:32.933 --> 31:35.519
Give her a flourish for me, young feller.

32:03.255 --> 32:05.883
"From the commander,
army of the united colonies to New York,

32:05.966 --> 32:08.344
"dispatch number 1,137."

32:08.427 --> 32:10.596
Sweet Jesus!

32:11.096 --> 32:12.741
"To the honorable congress,
John hancock, president.

32:12.765 --> 32:16.519
"Dear sir, it is with grave apprehension
that I have learned this day

32:16.602 --> 32:18.729
"of the sailing from halifax, Nova Scotia,

32:18.813 --> 32:22.233
"of a considerable force of British troops
in the company of foreign mercenaries

32:22.316 --> 32:24.902
"and under the command
of general sir William howe."

32:24.985 --> 32:27.446
"There can be no doubt
that their destination is New York,

32:27.530 --> 32:30.699
"for to take and hold this city
and the Hudson valley beyond

32:30.783 --> 32:33.619
"would serve to separate new england
from the rest of the colonies,

32:33.702 --> 32:36.747
"permitting both sections
to be crushed in turn.

32:36.831 --> 32:39.416
"Sadly, I see no way
of stopping them at the present time,

32:39.500 --> 32:41.877
"as my army is absolutely falling apart.

32:41.961 --> 32:43.963
"My military chest is totally exhausted.

32:44.046 --> 32:47.299
"My commissary general
has strained his credit to the last.

32:47.383 --> 32:50.970
"My quartermaster has no food,
no arms, no ammunition,

32:51.095 --> 32:54.014
"and my troops are in a
state of near mutiny.

32:54.098 --> 32:58.978
"L pray god some relief arrives
before the armada, but fear it will not.

32:59.061 --> 33:00.604
"Your obedient,

33:01.981 --> 33:03.399
"g. Washington."

33:04.191 --> 33:05.734
Mr. president!

33:05.818 --> 33:06.819
Colonel mckean.

33:06.902 --> 33:09.488
Surely we have managed to promote

33:09.572 --> 33:13.701
the gloomiest man on this continent
to the head of our troops.

33:13.784 --> 33:18.080
Those dispatches
are the most depressing accumulation

33:18.163 --> 33:23.460
of disaster, doom and despair
in the entire annals of military history.

33:24.169 --> 33:26.255
Colonel mckean, please!

33:26.338 --> 33:27.339
What?

33:28.340 --> 33:29.842
It's too hot.

33:31.051 --> 33:32.803
Well, I suppose so.

33:33.679 --> 33:37.892
General Washington will continue
wording his dispatches as he sees fit.

33:37.975 --> 33:39.935
And I'm sure we all pray

33:40.019 --> 33:43.939
he finds happier thoughts
to convey in the near future.

33:45.274 --> 33:47.109
Mr. thomson, are there any resolutions?

33:47.526 --> 33:49.695
Dr. Josiah bartlett of New Hampshire.

33:50.988 --> 33:54.158
"Resolved, that for the duration
of the present hostilities,

33:54.241 --> 33:57.620
"the congress discourage
every type of extravagance and dissipation,

33:57.703 --> 34:00.331
"elaborate funerals
and other expensive diversions,

34:00.414 --> 34:03.334
"especially all horse racing, gambling,

34:03.417 --> 34:06.086
"and other forms of sinful
activity, which..."

34:06.170 --> 34:07.630
Fire wagon!

34:24.813 --> 34:26.398
Where's the fire? Can anybody tell?

34:26.482 --> 34:29.121
- Looks like the Pemberton house.
- It couldn't be. It's brand new.

34:29.193 --> 34:32.571
- It might be the city tavern.
- Bite your tongue, man.

34:41.914 --> 34:43.290
Benjy, I'm back!

34:43.916 --> 34:47.002
- L'm back, Johnny!
- Richard, lad, welcome back.

34:50.880 --> 34:51.882
Lee, is it done?

34:51.966 --> 34:53.759
First things first. Tom!

34:53.842 --> 34:58.222
Tom! Tom, your little bride wants to know,
"when's he coming home?"

34:58.305 --> 34:59.390
I leave tonight.

34:59.473 --> 35:01.016
Never mind that, man. Ls it done?

35:01.100 --> 35:03.268
Done? Why, certain-Lee.

35:04.103 --> 35:07.856
Mr. president, I have returned from
Virginia with the following resolution,

35:07.940 --> 35:11.485
"resolved, that these united colonies are,
and of a right ought to be,

35:11.568 --> 35:13.028
"free and independent states,

35:13.112 --> 35:15.823
"that they are absolved
from allegiance to the British crown,

35:15.906 --> 35:19.284
"and that all political connection between
them and the state of Great Britain is,

35:19.368 --> 35:22.037
"and ought to be, totally dissolved."

35:22.121 --> 35:23.288
Hear, hear!

35:23.372 --> 35:26.166
Mr. president, I second the proposal.

35:26.250 --> 35:28.127
The resolution has been proposed
and seconded.

35:28.210 --> 35:30.754
The chair will now entertain debate.

35:31.672 --> 35:33.298
- Mr. Dickinson.
- Mr. president.

35:33.590 --> 35:35.718
Pennsylvania moves, as always,

35:35.801 --> 35:39.930
that the question
of independence be postponed indefinitely.

35:40.014 --> 35:41.807
I second the motion.

35:42.266 --> 35:43.726
Judge Wilson,

35:44.309 --> 35:47.062
in your eagerness to be loved,
you seem to have forgotten

35:47.146 --> 35:50.107
that Pennsylvania
cannot second its own motion.

35:51.525 --> 35:53.235
Delaware seconds.

35:53.318 --> 35:55.612
You would, you lousy wart.

35:56.155 --> 35:59.324
The motion to postpone
has been moved and seconded.

35:59.408 --> 36:00.826
Mr. thomson.

36:02.327 --> 36:04.121
On the motion to postpone indefinitely

36:04.204 --> 36:07.041
the resolution on independency
or proceed with the debate,

36:07.124 --> 36:08.792
all those in favor of debate say "yea,"

36:08.876 --> 36:10.419
all those for postponement say "nay."

36:10.502 --> 36:11.587
New Hampshire?

36:12.504 --> 36:14.715
New Hampshire favors debate, and says yea.

36:17.009 --> 36:19.178
New Hampshire says yea. Massachusetts?

36:19.762 --> 36:24.266
Massachusetts, having borne the brunt
of the king's tyranny...

36:24.349 --> 36:26.351
Yes, I said tyranny!

36:27.102 --> 36:30.105
Massachusetts now,
and for all time, says yea.

36:31.690 --> 36:33.525
Massachusetts says yea.

36:33.859 --> 36:35.360
Rhode Island?

36:36.361 --> 36:37.780
Mr. Hopkins?

36:38.530 --> 36:39.907
Where's Rhode Island?

36:39.990 --> 36:42.951
Rhode Island is out visiting the necessary.

36:43.243 --> 36:46.580
After what Rhode Island's consumed,
i can't say I'm surprised.

36:46.663 --> 36:48.582
We'll come back to him, Mr. thomson.

36:48.665 --> 36:50.417
Rhode Island passes.

36:55.172 --> 36:56.298
Connecticut?

36:58.383 --> 37:00.969
While Connecticut has, till now,

37:01.053 --> 37:03.305
been against this proposal,

37:03.889 --> 37:06.350
our legislature
has instructed me that in the event

37:06.433 --> 37:09.645
it is introduced by any colony
outside of new england,

37:09.728 --> 37:13.107
we could not any longer
withhold our support. Connecticut says yea.

37:13.190 --> 37:14.316
Hear! Hear!

37:14.399 --> 37:16.735
Connecticut says yea. New York?

37:18.237 --> 37:20.656
New York abstains courteously.

37:20.906 --> 37:22.407
New York abstains.

37:22.491 --> 37:23.534
Courteously.

37:25.744 --> 37:26.829
New Jersey?

37:26.912 --> 37:28.330
Absent, Mr. secretary.

37:30.415 --> 37:32.292
New Jersey's absent. Pennsylvania?

37:33.085 --> 37:36.630
Pennsylvania, for the 24th time, says nay.

37:36.713 --> 37:38.882
Pennsylvania says nay. Delaware?

37:39.925 --> 37:44.680
Delaware, as ever for independence,
says yea.

37:44.763 --> 37:47.182
Delaware says yea. Maryland?

37:48.100 --> 37:51.478
Maryland would welcome independence
if it were given,

37:51.562 --> 37:54.773
but is highly skeptical
that it can be taken.

37:54.857 --> 37:56.525
Maryland says nay.

37:58.318 --> 38:00.529
Maryland says nay. Virginia?

38:00.612 --> 38:03.365
Virginia, the first colony, says yea!

38:06.702 --> 38:09.037
Virginia says yea. North Carolina?

38:09.121 --> 38:13.417
North Carolina
respectfully yields to south Carolina.

38:13.500 --> 38:14.543
South Carolina?

38:14.626 --> 38:16.128
Mr. president,

38:16.712 --> 38:20.257
although we of south Carolina
have never seriously considered

38:20.340 --> 38:22.551
the question of independence,

38:22.634 --> 38:26.471
when a gentleman proposes it,
attention must be paid.

38:28.098 --> 38:31.685
However, we in the deep south,

38:31.768 --> 38:33.729
unlike our friends in new england,

38:33.812 --> 38:37.441
have no cause for impatience
at the present time.

38:38.567 --> 38:41.904
If at some future date it becomes the
wish of all our sister colonies,

38:41.987 --> 38:45.908
to effect a separation,
we will not stand in the way.

38:45.991 --> 38:47.826
But for the time being,

38:47.910 --> 38:51.121
south Carolina will wait and watch.

38:52.122 --> 38:53.707
The vote is nay.

38:56.001 --> 38:57.044
North Carolina...

38:57.127 --> 38:59.463
Says nay. Yes, Mr. Hewes. I know.

39:02.090 --> 39:03.133
Georgia.

39:06.553 --> 39:07.804
Georgia.

39:09.389 --> 39:14.269
Mr. president, Georgia seems to be split
right down the middle on this issue.

39:14.353 --> 39:17.189
The people are against it, and I'm for it.

39:19.650 --> 39:22.903
However, I'm afraid I'm not quite certain

39:22.986 --> 39:27.115
whether representing the people means
relying on theirjudgment or on my own.

39:27.199 --> 39:31.912
In all fairness, until I can figure that
out, I'd better lean a little on their side.

39:31.995 --> 39:33.205
Georgia says nay.

39:37.876 --> 39:39.962
Georgia says nay.

39:40.045 --> 39:41.588
Rhode Island?

39:43.507 --> 39:45.926
Second call, Rhode Island!

39:46.551 --> 39:48.262
Rhode Island!

39:48.512 --> 39:50.973
I'm coming! I'm coming!

39:51.223 --> 39:53.350
Hold your damn horses.

39:53.433 --> 39:56.937
- We're waiting on you, Mr. Hopkins.
- Well, it won't kill you.

39:57.020 --> 40:00.482
You'd think the congress
would have its own privy.

40:00.565 --> 40:02.609
All right, where does she stand?

40:02.693 --> 40:06.530
Five for debate, five for postponement,
one abstention and one absence.

40:06.613 --> 40:08.407
So it's up to me, huh?

40:08.490 --> 40:10.534
Well, I'll tell you.

40:10.617 --> 40:15.080
In all my years,
i never seen, heard nor smelled an issue

40:15.163 --> 40:18.000
that was so dangerous
it couldn't be talked about.

40:18.083 --> 40:21.837
Hell, yes! I'm for debating anything.
Rhode Island says yea.

40:24.673 --> 40:27.926
- Mcnair, get Mr. Hopkins a rum.
- But you said...

40:28.010 --> 40:30.679
Get him the whole damn barrel if he wants.

40:31.638 --> 40:34.057
The chair now declares this congress
a committee of the whole

40:34.141 --> 40:37.561
for the purpose of debating
Virginia's resolution on independence.

40:37.644 --> 40:39.146
Mr. Dickinson.

40:41.023 --> 40:45.986
Well, now,
you've got your way at last, Mr. Adams.

40:46.361 --> 40:48.697
The matter may now be discussed.

40:49.531 --> 40:51.992
I confess I'm almost relieved.

40:52.659 --> 40:56.163
There's a question
I've been fairly itching to ask you.

40:58.540 --> 40:59.624
Why?

40:59.708 --> 41:01.918
Why what, Mr. Dickinson?

41:02.002 --> 41:04.671
Well, why independence, Mr. Adams?

41:05.172 --> 41:08.091
Well, for the obvious reason
that our continued association

41:08.175 --> 41:11.053
with Great Britain has grown intolerable.

41:11.136 --> 41:13.680
Well, to whom, Mr. Adams? To you?

41:14.639 --> 41:17.601
Well, then I suggest
you sever your ties immediately.

41:17.684 --> 41:22.898
But please be kind enough
to leave the rest of us where we are.

41:23.690 --> 41:25.692
For myself, I have no objection at all

41:25.776 --> 41:28.487
to being part of the greatest
empire on earth,

41:28.570 --> 41:31.531
to enjoying its protection
and sharing its benefits.

41:31.615 --> 41:32.866
Benefits?

41:34.076 --> 41:35.535
What benefits?

41:36.203 --> 41:39.414
Crippling taxes? Cruel repressions?

41:39.498 --> 41:41.124
Abolished rights?

41:42.876 --> 41:46.797
Is that all england means to you, sir?

41:48.924 --> 41:52.135
Is that all
the pride and affection you can muster

41:52.219 --> 41:54.638
for the nation that bore you?

41:54.721 --> 41:58.475
For the noblest, most civilized nation
on the face of this planet?

41:58.558 --> 42:02.187
Well, would you have us forsake
Hastings and magna carta,

42:02.270 --> 42:05.857
strongbow and lionheart,
Drake and marlborough,

42:05.941 --> 42:07.943
tudors, Stuarts and plantagenets?

42:08.026 --> 42:09.653
For what, sir?

42:09.736 --> 42:11.738
Well, tell me. For what?

42:14.991 --> 42:16.243
For you?

42:19.746 --> 42:23.875
Some men are patriots,
like general Washington,

42:23.959 --> 42:26.169
and some are anarchists, like Mr. paine.

42:26.253 --> 42:29.005
Some even are internationalists,
like Dr. Franklin.

42:29.089 --> 42:31.633
But you, sir...

42:33.260 --> 42:36.012
You are merely an agitator,

42:36.096 --> 42:37.514
disturbing the peace,

42:37.597 --> 42:40.058
creating disorder,
endangering the public welfare.

42:40.142 --> 42:41.518
And for what?

42:41.601 --> 42:43.895
Your petty little personal complaints.

42:43.979 --> 42:46.022
Your taxes are too high.

42:47.649 --> 42:51.403
Well, sir, so are mine.

42:54.239 --> 42:56.449
Come, come, Mr. Adams.

42:57.075 --> 43:00.453
If you have grievances,
and I'm sure you have,

43:00.537 --> 43:04.040
our present system must provide
a gentler means of redressing them

43:04.124 --> 43:06.126
short of revolution.

43:07.043 --> 43:09.212
Yes, that's what he wants.

43:09.296 --> 43:11.214
Nothing less will satisfy him.

43:11.298 --> 43:14.092
Violence, rebellion, treason.

43:16.595 --> 43:18.638
Now, Mr. Adams,

43:19.806 --> 43:22.976
are these the acts of englishmen?

43:23.059 --> 43:25.604
Not englishmen, Dickinson. Americans.

43:25.687 --> 43:27.647
No, sir. Englishmen!

43:28.440 --> 43:30.400
Please, Mr. Dickinson,
must you start banging?

43:30.483 --> 43:31.735
How is a man to sleep?

43:33.320 --> 43:36.781
Forgive me, Dr. Franklin,
but must you start speaking?

43:36.865 --> 43:38.992
How is a man to stay awake?

43:40.493 --> 43:42.579
We'll promise to be quiet, sir.

43:42.662 --> 43:45.874
I'm sure everyone prefers
that you remain asleep.

43:46.208 --> 43:48.293
If I'm to hear myself
called an englishman, sir,

43:48.376 --> 43:50.378
I assure you I prefer I'd remained asleep.

43:51.671 --> 43:54.257
Now, what's so terrible
about being called an englishman?

43:54.341 --> 43:55.884
The English don't seem to mind.

43:56.218 --> 43:59.596
Nor would I, were I given the
full rights of an englishman.

43:59.679 --> 44:03.642
But to call me one without those rights
is like calling an ox a bull.

44:03.725 --> 44:07.270
He's thankful for the honor, but he'd much
rather have restored what's rightfully his.

44:13.902 --> 44:16.696
When did you first notice
they were missing, sir?

44:22.369 --> 44:25.205
Fortunately, the people of these colonies

44:25.288 --> 44:27.916
maintain a higher regard
for their mother country.

44:28.875 --> 44:31.795
Higher, certainly, than she feels for them.

44:31.878 --> 44:36.091
Never was such a valuable possession
so stupidly and so recklessly managed

44:36.174 --> 44:39.094
than this entire continent
by the British crown.

44:39.177 --> 44:42.347
Our industry discouraged,
our resources pillaged.

44:43.598 --> 44:46.393
Worst of all, our very character stifled.

44:47.060 --> 44:49.312
We've spawned a new race here,
Mr. Dickinson.

44:49.396 --> 44:50.730
Rougher, simpler,

44:50.814 --> 44:53.441
more violent, more enterprising,

44:53.525 --> 44:54.985
less refined.

44:55.610 --> 44:57.362
We're a new nationality.

44:57.445 --> 44:59.572
We require a new nation.

45:02.867 --> 45:03.952
Well,

45:04.744 --> 45:07.205
that may be your opinion, Dr. Franklin,

45:07.289 --> 45:12.752
but, as I said,
the people feel quite differently.

45:12.836 --> 45:16.214
Now, what do you know
about the people, Dickinson?

45:16.298 --> 45:19.884
You don't speak for the people.
You represent only yourself.

45:19.968 --> 45:22.053
And that precious status quo

45:22.137 --> 45:25.515
you keep imploring the people
to preserve for their own good

45:25.598 --> 45:29.728
is nothing more than the eternal
preservation of your own property.

45:31.271 --> 45:34.024
Mr. Adams, you have an annoying talent

45:34.107 --> 45:36.192
for making such delightful words

45:36.276 --> 45:39.487
as "property" sound quite distasteful.

45:39.571 --> 45:42.490
In heaven's name,
what's wrong with property?

45:43.199 --> 45:46.328
Perhaps you've forgotten
that many of us first came to these shores

45:46.411 --> 45:49.039
in order to secure rights to property,

45:49.122 --> 45:53.376
and that we hold these rights
no less dear than the rights you speak of.

45:53.460 --> 45:57.922
Yes. So safe, so fat,
so comfortable in Pennsylvania.

45:58.006 --> 46:00.383
And what is this independence of yours

46:00.467 --> 46:03.178
except the private grievance
of Massachusetts?

46:03.261 --> 46:05.972
Why is it always Boston
that breaks the king's peace?

46:06.056 --> 46:10.435
My dear congress,
you must not adopt this evil measure.

46:10.518 --> 46:12.729
It is the work of the devil.

46:12.812 --> 46:15.148
Leave it where it belongs.

46:15.982 --> 46:17.400
In new england.

46:17.484 --> 46:21.154
Brother Dickinson, new england has been
fighting the devil for more than 100 years.

46:21.696 --> 46:26.409
And as of now, brother sherman,
the devil has been winning hands down.

46:27.077 --> 46:30.413
Why, at this very moment,
he's sitting right here in this congress.

46:30.497 --> 46:34.334
Don't let him deceive you.
This proposal is entirely his doing.

46:34.417 --> 46:36.086
It may bear Virginia's name,

46:36.169 --> 46:40.090
but it reeks of Adams,
Adams and more Adams.

46:40.173 --> 46:45.470
Look at him. Ready to lead this continent
down the fiery path of total destruction.

46:45.553 --> 46:49.682
Good god! Why can't you acknowledge
what already exists?

46:49.766 --> 46:53.269
It has been more than a year
since Concord and Lexington.

46:53.353 --> 46:55.647
Damn it, man, we're at war, right now!

46:55.730 --> 46:58.983
You may be at war.
You, Boston and John Adams.

46:59.067 --> 47:01.694
But you will never speak for Pennsylvania.

47:01.778 --> 47:02.821
Nor for Delaware.

47:02.904 --> 47:07.283
Mr. read, you represent
only one-third of Delaware.

47:07.367 --> 47:09.452
The sensible third, Mr. Rodney.

47:09.536 --> 47:12.705
Sit down, you scurvy dog,
or I'll knock you down.

47:13.540 --> 47:14.958
Sit down, all three of you!

47:15.041 --> 47:17.043
Mcnair, do something about that damn dog!

47:17.127 --> 47:18.628
And here, fetch me a rum.

47:18.711 --> 47:20.797
- Get that dog first!
- Rum, rum!

47:20.880 --> 47:22.674
I only got two hands.

47:27.512 --> 47:29.222
Christ, it's hot!

47:41.609 --> 47:43.653
Please do go on, gentlemen.

47:43.736 --> 47:46.030
You're making the only breeze
in Philadelphia.

47:47.782 --> 47:49.117
Mr. Adams,

47:49.784 --> 47:52.704
perhaps you could
clear up something for me?

47:53.371 --> 47:55.498
After we have achieved independence,

47:55.582 --> 47:58.251
who do you propose
would govern in south Carolina?

48:00.044 --> 48:01.588
The people, of course.

48:02.130 --> 48:04.966
Which people, sir?
The people of south Carolina

48:05.091 --> 48:07.385
or the people of Massachusetts?

48:07.719 --> 48:09.220
Why don't you admit it, neddy?

48:09.304 --> 48:12.223
You're against independence now
and you always will be.

48:12.307 --> 48:13.600
Aye.

48:15.727 --> 48:19.314
Gentlemen, you refuse to understand us.

48:19.397 --> 48:22.150
We desire independence. Yes.

48:23.109 --> 48:25.820
For south Carolina. That is our country.

48:27.113 --> 48:30.200
And as such,
we don't wish to belong to anyone.

48:30.283 --> 48:32.952
Not to england and not to you.

48:34.120 --> 48:36.748
We intend to have one nation, Rutledge.

48:36.831 --> 48:40.043
A nation of sovereign states, Mr. Adams.

48:40.126 --> 48:45.715
United for our mutual protection,
but separate for our individual pursuits.

48:45.798 --> 48:48.760
Now, that is what
we have understood it to be,

48:48.843 --> 48:51.638
and that is what we will support.

48:53.139 --> 48:55.642
As soon as everyone supports it.

48:59.646 --> 49:01.981
Well, there you are, Mr. Adams.

49:02.774 --> 49:05.068
You must see that we need time.

49:05.568 --> 49:10.615
Time to make certain who we are and where
we stand in regard to one another.

49:10.698 --> 49:14.661
For if we do not determine the nature
of the beast before we set it free,

49:14.744 --> 49:17.413
it will end by consuming us all.

49:17.497 --> 49:19.707
For once in your life, Wilson,

49:20.667 --> 49:22.168
take a chance.

49:23.795 --> 49:25.672
I say the time is now.

49:26.839 --> 49:28.800
It may never come again.

49:29.551 --> 49:33.304
Your clock is fast, Mr. Adams.
I say we're not yet ripe for independence.

49:33.513 --> 49:36.724
Not ripe? Hell, we're
rotting for want of it.

49:37.308 --> 49:41.187
Gentlemen, please,
what in god's name is the infernal hurry?

49:41.271 --> 49:43.273
Why must this question be settled now?

49:43.356 --> 49:45.608
What's wrong with now, Mr. chase?

49:45.858 --> 49:48.069
General Washington is in the field.

49:48.152 --> 49:52.282
If he's defeated, as it now appears,
we'll be inviting the hangman.

49:52.365 --> 49:56.452
But if, by some miracle,
he should actually win,

49:56.536 --> 49:59.247
we can then declare anything
we damn please.

49:59.330 --> 50:02.166
The sentiments of north Carolina precisely.

50:02.875 --> 50:05.003
Has it ever occurred to either of you

50:05.086 --> 50:09.549
that an army needs something
to fight for in order to win?

50:09.716 --> 50:13.136
A purpose? A goal? A flag of its own?

50:13.595 --> 50:14.929
Mr. Adams,

50:15.847 --> 50:21.185
how can a nation of only 2 million souls
stand up to an empire of 10 million?

50:21.269 --> 50:22.687
Think of it. 10 million.

50:22.770 --> 50:25.106
How do we compensate for that shortage?

50:25.189 --> 50:27.900
It's simple, Mr. chase.
Increase and multiply.

50:27.984 --> 50:29.360
How's that?

50:30.695 --> 50:33.489
We will more than compensate with spirit.

50:33.865 --> 50:36.659
I tell you, there is
a spirit out there among the people

50:36.743 --> 50:38.828
that is sadly lacking in this congress.

50:38.911 --> 50:41.956
Yes, of course. Now it's spirit.

50:42.040 --> 50:44.042
Well, why didn't I think of that?

50:44.125 --> 50:48.254
No army, no Navy, no arms, no ammunition,

50:48.338 --> 50:52.634
no treasury, no friends,

50:52.717 --> 50:55.803
but, bless our soul, spirit.

50:56.804 --> 50:59.223
Mr. Lee, Mr. Hopkins,

50:59.307 --> 51:01.726
Mr. Rodney, colonel mckean,

51:01.809 --> 51:03.311
Dr. Franklin.

51:04.604 --> 51:08.900
Why have you joined
this incendiary little man,

51:09.651 --> 51:11.736
this Boston radical,

51:13.029 --> 51:14.530
this agitator,

51:15.907 --> 51:17.450
this demagogue,

51:17.950 --> 51:19.619
this madman?

51:19.702 --> 51:22.205
Are you calling me a madman, you...

51:23.456 --> 51:24.874
You fribble!

51:27.043 --> 51:29.962
You and your Pennsylvania proprietors,

51:30.046 --> 51:33.007
you cool, considerate men,

51:33.091 --> 51:35.259
you hang to the rear on every issue,

51:35.343 --> 51:38.721
so that if we should go under,
you'll still remain afloat.

51:38.805 --> 51:40.640
Are you calling me a coward?

51:41.307 --> 51:42.975
Yes. Coward!

51:43.685 --> 51:44.727
Madman!

51:44.811 --> 51:45.895
Landlord!

51:45.978 --> 51:47.230
Lawyer!

51:53.695 --> 51:55.655
Stop it! Stop it!

51:57.448 --> 52:00.743
This is the congress. Stop it, I say!

52:00.827 --> 52:02.078
The enemy's out there.

52:02.161 --> 52:03.830
No, Mr. Rodney, the enemy is here.

52:03.913 --> 52:06.749
No. I say he's out there.

52:06.833 --> 52:08.459
England.

52:08.543 --> 52:12.046
England closing in, cutting off our air.

52:12.130 --> 52:13.715
There's no time!

52:17.301 --> 52:18.511
No air.

52:19.846 --> 52:21.139
Dr. hall.

52:25.226 --> 52:26.728
Colonel mckean.

52:26.811 --> 52:28.604
Aye. It's the cancer.

52:29.731 --> 52:31.607
But he should go home.

52:32.608 --> 52:35.820
A man should die in his own bed.

52:37.488 --> 52:39.699
John. John Adams.

52:39.782 --> 52:41.409
I'm here, Caesar.

52:44.203 --> 52:46.289
I leave you

52:46.372 --> 52:48.666
a divided Delaware.

52:49.917 --> 52:51.294
Forgive me.

52:52.003 --> 52:54.088
I'll take you home, Caesar.

53:18.905 --> 53:21.115
I'll be back within the week.

53:28.706 --> 53:32.126
Mr. president,
south Carolina calls the question.

53:34.170 --> 53:35.379
What's that, Mr. Rutledge?

53:36.589 --> 53:38.633
I said, Mr. president,

53:38.716 --> 53:42.136
south Carolina desires to end the debate

53:43.763 --> 53:46.182
and calls the question of independence.

53:46.265 --> 53:48.476
- Delaware seconds.
- Thank you.

53:49.936 --> 53:52.980
Gentlemen, please!

53:53.064 --> 53:55.900
The question has been called and seconded.

53:56.984 --> 53:59.028
The secretary will record the vote.

53:59.111 --> 54:01.447
Franklin, do something. Think.

54:01.531 --> 54:03.533
I'm thinking, but nothing's coming.

54:03.616 --> 54:05.743
All those in favor
of the resolution on independence

54:05.827 --> 54:08.371
as proposed by the colony of Virginia,
signify by saying...

54:08.454 --> 54:09.956
Mr. secretary.

54:10.748 --> 54:12.708
Will you please read the resolution again?

54:12.792 --> 54:13.918
What?

54:15.127 --> 54:16.295
I've forgotten it.

54:16.379 --> 54:17.964
Now, Benjamin...

54:20.466 --> 54:23.177
"Resolved, that these united colonies are,

54:23.261 --> 54:25.888
"and of a right ought to be,
free and independent..."

54:32.270 --> 54:35.857
Excuse me.
Ls this the continental congress?

54:35.940 --> 54:38.526
Yes, I can see that it must be.

54:39.735 --> 54:41.863
It's all right. We found it.

54:42.363 --> 54:44.740
We've been looking
for you everywhere, you see.

54:44.824 --> 54:47.451
Someone told us
that you might be at carpenters' hall

54:47.535 --> 54:50.162
and someone else suggested library hall,
and...

54:50.246 --> 54:51.914
So, finally, we asked a constable...

54:51.998 --> 54:53.082
Excuse me, sir,

54:53.165 --> 54:56.252
but, if you don't mind,
the congress is about to decide

54:56.335 --> 54:58.337
the question of American independence.

54:59.463 --> 55:01.841
How splendid. That means
we're not too late.

55:01.924 --> 55:04.176
These gentlemen are Mr. Francis hopkinson,

55:04.260 --> 55:08.014
Mr. Richard stockton,
and I'm the reverend John Witherspoon.

55:11.392 --> 55:13.686
We're the new delegates from New Jersey.

55:13.936 --> 55:15.313
New Jersey?

55:19.525 --> 55:20.985
Dr. Franklin,

55:21.444 --> 55:25.072
I regret that I must be the bearer
of unhappy tidings, sir,

55:25.156 --> 55:27.950
but your son,
the royal governor of New Jersey,

55:28.034 --> 55:29.952
has been taken prisoner

55:30.036 --> 55:34.040
and has been moved under guard to the
colony of Connecticut for safekeeping.

55:34.123 --> 55:35.458
Is he unharmed, sir?

55:35.541 --> 55:37.335
When last I heard, he was. Yes, sir.

55:37.418 --> 55:41.130
Well, then why the long face? I hear
Connecticut is an excellent location.

55:41.213 --> 55:44.300
Tell me.
Why did they arrest the little bastard?

55:46.552 --> 55:47.678
Our...

55:48.262 --> 55:51.849
New Jersey legislature has recalled
the old delegation to this congress

55:51.933 --> 55:54.602
and has sent a new one.

55:55.561 --> 55:57.813
Quickly, man,
where do you stand on independence?

55:57.897 --> 55:59.607
- Well, haven't I made that clear?
- No.

55:59.690 --> 56:01.025
Well, I suppose I haven't.

56:01.108 --> 56:02.944
But that's the reason for the change.

56:03.027 --> 56:05.404
See, we've been instructed
to vote for independence.

56:05.488 --> 56:06.822
Mr. president!

56:06.906 --> 56:11.327
Massachusetts is now ready
for the vote on independence,

56:11.410 --> 56:15.831
and reminds the chair of its privilege
to decide all votes that are deadlocked.

56:15.915 --> 56:17.917
I won't forget, Mr. Adams.

56:19.377 --> 56:23.339
The chair takes this opportunity
to welcome the New Jersey delegation

56:23.422 --> 56:26.759
and appoints the reverend Witherspoon
congressional chaplain

56:26.842 --> 56:28.344
if he will accept the post.

56:28.427 --> 56:30.388
With much pleasure, sir.

56:32.348 --> 56:37.520
Very well. Mr. thomson, you may
now proceed with the vote on independence.

56:38.479 --> 56:40.690
All in favor
of the resolution on independence

56:40.773 --> 56:43.043
as proposed by the colony of Virginia,
signify by saying...

56:43.067 --> 56:44.110
Mr. president.

56:45.861 --> 56:49.991
Pennsylvania moves
that any vote in favor of independence

56:51.409 --> 56:53.202
must be unanimous.

56:53.869 --> 56:54.912
What?

56:55.371 --> 56:56.706
I second the motion.

56:56.789 --> 56:58.207
Judge Wilson!

56:58.624 --> 56:59.959
Oh, my god.

57:00.584 --> 57:02.253
Delaware seconds, Mr. president.

57:02.336 --> 57:05.006
No vote has ever had to be unanimous,
Dickinson, and you know it.

57:05.089 --> 57:07.550
- Yes, but this one must be.
- On what grounds?

57:07.633 --> 57:11.345
That no colony be torn from
its mother country without its own consent.

57:11.429 --> 57:12.805
Hear! Hear!

57:13.222 --> 57:16.100
But it will never be unanimous, damn it.

57:17.101 --> 57:19.311
If you say so, Mr. Adams.

57:21.188 --> 57:24.358
It has been moved and seconded
that the vote on independence

57:24.442 --> 57:26.736
must be unanimous in order to carry.

57:26.819 --> 57:29.321
All those in favor, signify by saying yea.

57:29.405 --> 57:30.406
Yea!

57:30.489 --> 57:34.994
One, two, three, four, five, six.

57:35.077 --> 57:37.371
Six colonies say yea. Against?

57:37.455 --> 57:38.539
Nay!

57:38.622 --> 57:43.002
One, two, three, four, five, six.

57:43.252 --> 57:45.046
Six colonies say nay.

57:46.088 --> 57:50.760
Mr. secretary,
New York abstains courteously.

57:50.843 --> 57:55.264
Mr. Morris,
why does New York constantly abstain?

57:55.347 --> 57:58.267
Why doesn't New York
simply stay in New York?

57:59.685 --> 58:01.812
Very well. The vote is tied.

58:03.064 --> 58:06.484
The principles of independence
have no greater advocate in congress

58:06.567 --> 58:08.319
than its president.

58:08.861 --> 58:12.198
That is why I must join those
who vote for unanimity.

58:12.948 --> 58:15.409
Good god, John!
What are you doing? You've sunk us.

58:15.493 --> 58:17.203
Now, hear me out.

58:17.286 --> 58:19.789
Don't you see that any colony
who opposes independence

58:19.872 --> 58:21.683
will be forced to fight
on the side of england?

58:21.707 --> 58:24.460
That we'll be setting
brother against brother,

58:24.543 --> 58:28.380
that our new nation will carry
as its emblem the mark of Cain.

58:29.215 --> 58:30.841
I can see no other way.

58:30.925 --> 58:35.054
Either we all walk together,
or together we must stay where we are.

58:37.098 --> 58:38.808
The man's from Massachusetts.

58:38.891 --> 58:41.102
Very well. Proceed, Mr. thomson.

58:41.185 --> 58:43.771
A unanimous vote being necessary to carry,

58:43.854 --> 58:46.357
if any be opposed
to the resolution on independence

58:46.440 --> 58:48.567
as proposed by the colony of Virginia,
signify by...

58:48.651 --> 58:49.652
Mr. president.

58:49.735 --> 58:52.363
For heaven's sake,
let me get through it once.

58:52.446 --> 58:53.948
Mr. president.

58:55.241 --> 58:56.742
I move for a postponement.

58:56.826 --> 58:57.993
Postponement?

58:58.077 --> 58:59.954
I wish you the same luck I had with it.

59:00.037 --> 59:01.997
Mr. Adams is right. We need a postponement.

59:02.081 --> 59:03.374
On what grounds?

59:03.457 --> 59:05.084
On what grounds?

59:05.626 --> 59:09.922
Mr. president, how can this congress vote
onindependence

59:10.005 --> 59:14.885
without a written declaration
of some sort defining it?

59:16.595 --> 59:18.514
What sort of declaration?

59:20.099 --> 59:24.186
Well, you know,
listing the reasons for the separation,

59:24.270 --> 59:27.273
our purposes, goals, so forth, so on.

59:27.356 --> 59:29.733
- Ditto, ditto.
- Ditto, ditto, et cetera, et cetera.

59:29.817 --> 59:31.318
We know those, don't we?

59:33.654 --> 59:35.781
Yes, good god, we know them,

59:36.782 --> 59:39.034
but what about the rest of the world?

59:39.118 --> 59:41.537
Certainly we require the assistance

59:41.620 --> 59:45.207
of a powerful nation
such as France or Spain.

59:45.291 --> 59:49.795
And such a written declaration
would be consistent with European delicacy.

59:51.297 --> 59:54.550
Come now, Mr. Adams.
You'll have to do better than that.

59:54.633 --> 59:57.553
Answer straight. What would be its purpose?

59:58.512 --> 01:00:00.556
Yes. Well...

01:00:03.392 --> 01:00:07.521
To place before mankind
the common sense of the subject

01:00:08.439 --> 01:00:11.150
in terms so plain and firm

01:00:11.775 --> 01:00:13.861
as to command their assent.

01:00:21.577 --> 01:00:24.747
Mr. Jefferson, are you seriously suggesting

01:00:24.830 --> 01:00:27.791
that we publish a paper
declaring to all the world

01:00:27.875 --> 01:00:32.171
that an illegal rebellion
is, in reality, a legal one?

01:00:32.254 --> 01:00:35.090
Mr. Dickinson, I'm surprised at you.

01:00:35.174 --> 01:00:37.927
You should know that rebellion
is always legal in the first person,

01:00:38.010 --> 01:00:39.720
such as "our rebellion."

01:00:39.803 --> 01:00:42.765
It's only in the third person, "their
rebellion," that it is illegal.

01:00:45.059 --> 01:00:47.269
Mr. president, I second the motion

01:00:47.353 --> 01:00:49.104
to postpone the vote on independence

01:00:49.188 --> 01:00:53.025
for a period of time sufficient
for the writing of a declaration.

01:00:53.359 --> 01:00:55.361
It has been moved and seconded.
Mr. thomson.

01:00:55.444 --> 01:00:58.948
All those in favor of the motion to
postpone, signify by saying yea.

01:00:59.031 --> 01:01:00.532
Yea!

01:01:00.616 --> 01:01:04.870
One, two, three, four, five, six.

01:01:04.954 --> 01:01:06.914
Six colonies say yea. Against?

01:01:06.997 --> 01:01:07.998
Nay!

01:01:08.082 --> 01:01:12.336
One, two, three, four, five, six.

01:01:12.753 --> 01:01:14.546
Six colonies say nay.

01:01:16.966 --> 01:01:20.761
Mr. secretary,
New York abstains courteously.

01:01:25.391 --> 01:01:28.852
Mr. Morris, what in hell
goes on in New York?

01:01:29.853 --> 01:01:33.399
I'm sorry, Mr. president,
but the simple fact is that

01:01:33.482 --> 01:01:37.903
our legislature has never
sent us explicit instructions on anything.

01:01:38.946 --> 01:01:40.114
Never?

01:01:41.448 --> 01:01:43.117
That's impossible.

01:01:44.785 --> 01:01:49.790
Mr. president, have you ever been present
at a meeting of the New York legislature?

01:01:50.374 --> 01:01:52.626
They speak very fast and very loud,

01:01:52.710 --> 01:01:55.254
and nobody listens to anybody else

01:01:55.337 --> 01:01:58.257
with the result that
nothing ever gets done.

01:02:00.843 --> 01:02:02.928
I beg the congress' pardon.

01:02:05.222 --> 01:02:07.266
My sympathies, Mr. Morris.

01:02:07.933 --> 01:02:11.687
The vote again being tied,
the chair decides in favor of postponement.

01:02:11.770 --> 01:02:13.522
So ruled.

01:02:13.605 --> 01:02:15.750
A committee will now be formed
to manage the declaration.

01:02:15.774 --> 01:02:18.736
Said document to be written,
debated, approved by the beginning of July,

01:02:18.819 --> 01:02:20.571
some three weeks hence.

01:02:20.654 --> 01:02:25.534
At which time, Virginia's resolution
on independence will finally be voted.

01:02:25.617 --> 01:02:27.119
Is that clear?

01:02:27.953 --> 01:02:31.206
Very well. Will the following gentlemen
serve on the declaration committee,

01:02:31.290 --> 01:02:33.042
- Dr. Franklin?
- Gladly.

01:02:33.417 --> 01:02:35.294
- Mr. John Adams?
- Yes.

01:02:35.419 --> 01:02:36.503
Mr. sherman?

01:02:37.504 --> 01:02:39.298
- Mr. Livingston?
- Right.

01:02:39.381 --> 01:02:41.258
And, of course, Mr. Lee.

01:02:41.800 --> 01:02:45.596
Excuse me, but I must be returning
to the sovereign colony of Virginia

01:02:45.679 --> 01:02:48.098
as I have been asked to serve as governor.

01:02:48.182 --> 01:02:51.810
And therefore I must
decline respectful-Lee.

01:02:56.648 --> 01:02:58.776
Very well, Mr. Lee, you're excused then.

01:02:58.859 --> 01:03:01.362
I suppose we could leave it
a four-man committee.

01:03:01.445 --> 01:03:03.739
Just a moment.
This business needs a virginian.

01:03:03.822 --> 01:03:05.449
Therefore I propose a replacement.

01:03:05.532 --> 01:03:07.326
- Mr. Thomas Jefferson.
- No. Mr. Adams...

01:03:07.409 --> 01:03:09.578
Very well, Mr. Adams.
Mr. Jefferson will serve.

01:03:09.661 --> 01:03:12.331
- L'm going home, too, to my wife.
- Move to adjourn!

01:03:12.414 --> 01:03:13.499
- Wait.
- Lsecond.

01:03:13.582 --> 01:03:17.252
Mr. hancock,
i haven't seen her for six months.

01:03:17.336 --> 01:03:19.213
Moved and seconded. Any objections?

01:03:19.296 --> 01:03:21.382
I have objections. I
have lots of objections.

01:03:21.465 --> 01:03:23.675
So ruled! Congress stands adjourned!

01:03:23.759 --> 01:03:26.095
John, I need to see my wife.

01:03:26.178 --> 01:03:27.805
It's all right. Come along, come along.

01:03:27.888 --> 01:03:29.848
No. I'm going home tonight.

01:03:29.932 --> 01:03:31.517
Of course you are. Of course.

01:03:31.600 --> 01:03:34.478
Mcnair, some rum up to my office.

01:03:36.021 --> 01:03:38.023
Don't worry, tom.

01:03:38.107 --> 01:03:39.775
Let me handle it.

01:03:39.858 --> 01:03:41.693
I'll get Adams to write it.

01:03:41.777 --> 01:03:44.154
I don't know.
He had a funny look on his face.

01:03:44.238 --> 01:03:45.364
He always does.

01:03:45.447 --> 01:03:46.740
All right, gentlemen,

