01:14:48.485 --> 01:14:50.278
- Have you eaten?
- Not yet, but...

01:14:50.361 --> 01:14:52.361
I understand
the Turkey's fresh at bunch of grapes.

01:14:52.530 --> 01:14:55.450
Well, the fact is I have
a rendezvous, John.

01:14:55.533 --> 01:14:58.703
I'd ask you along,
but talking makes her nervous.

01:15:01.414 --> 01:15:02.957
Yes, of course.

01:15:22.811 --> 01:15:24.229
Incredible.

01:15:32.237 --> 01:15:33.488
Abigail?

01:15:34.823 --> 01:15:36.825
I'm very lonely, Abigail.

01:15:37.575 --> 01:15:38.952
<i>Are you, John?</i>

01:15:39.035 --> 01:15:42.497
<i>As long as you were sending for wives,
why didn't you send for your own?</i>

01:15:42.580 --> 01:15:45.500
Now, don't be unreasonable, Abigail.

01:15:45.583 --> 01:15:47.418
<i>Now I'm unreasonable.</i>

01:15:47.752 --> 01:15:50.088
<i>You must add that to your list.</i>

01:15:51.256 --> 01:15:52.674
List?

01:15:52.757 --> 01:15:55.927
The catalog of my faults
you included in your last letter.

01:15:57.554 --> 01:16:01.141
They were fondly intended, madam.

01:16:01.224 --> 01:16:02.851
That I play at cards badly?

01:16:02.934 --> 01:16:04.352
A compliment.

01:16:04.435 --> 01:16:06.229
That my posture is crooked?

01:16:06.855 --> 01:16:08.857
An endearment.

01:16:08.940 --> 01:16:10.817
That I read, write and think too much?

01:16:10.900 --> 01:16:12.944
An irony.

01:16:13.027 --> 01:16:14.404
