01:20:17.271 --> 01:20:19.399
Your voice is more piercing.

01:20:21.818 --> 01:20:24.362
John, look at her. Just look at her.

01:20:24.445 --> 01:20:25.655
Lam.

01:20:25.738 --> 01:20:28.658
She's even more magnificent
than I remember.

01:20:30.159 --> 01:20:32.870
Of course, we didn't see
much of her front last night.

01:20:32.954 --> 01:20:34.205
Good morrow, madam.

01:20:34.288 --> 01:20:35.706
Good morrow.

01:20:38.251 --> 01:20:42.171
Is it the habit in Philadelphia for strangers
to shout at ladies from the street?

01:20:42.255 --> 01:20:43.464
Not really, but...

01:20:43.548 --> 01:20:48.010
And for men of your age
it is not only unseemly, it is unsightly.

01:20:49.220 --> 01:20:52.432
Excuse me, madam, but we met last evening.

01:20:53.558 --> 01:20:55.226
I spoke to no one last evening.

01:20:55.309 --> 01:20:56.561
Indeed, you did not.

01:20:56.644 --> 01:20:59.313
Nonetheless, we did present ourselves.

01:20:59.397 --> 01:21:02.358
This is Mr. John Adams.
I'm Dr. Benjamin Franklin.

01:21:03.776 --> 01:21:05.194
The inventor of the stove.

01:21:07.238 --> 01:21:10.575
Please! I know your names very well, but...

01:21:10.658 --> 01:21:13.077
Well, you said
you presented yourselves last night?

01:21:13.161 --> 01:21:15.913
It's of no matter.
Your thoughts were well-taken elsewhere.

01:21:19.000 --> 01:21:20.918
My husband is not yet up.

01:21:21.002 --> 01:21:23.421
Well, then shall we start over again?
Won't you join us?

01:21:24.255 --> 01:21:26.007
Yes, of course.

01:21:28.259 --> 01:21:29.778
Well, no wonder the man couldn't write.

01:21:29.802 --> 01:21:31.762
Who would think
of independence married to her?

01:21:31.846 --> 01:21:34.098
- I feel an absolute fool.
- That's good for you, John.

01:21:34.182 --> 01:21:36.100
I tell you, Franklin,
it's positively indecent.

01:21:36.184 --> 01:21:39.854
- John, they're young and they're in love.
- Not them, Franklin. Us.

01:21:39.937 --> 01:21:43.107
Standing down here, waiting for them to...

01:21:44.275 --> 01:21:46.152
Well, what will people think?

01:21:46.235 --> 01:21:49.530
Don't worry, John.
The history books will clean it up.

01:21:49.614 --> 01:21:50.781
Well, it doesn't matter.

01:21:51.115 --> 01:21:54.535
I'll not appear in the history
books anyway. Only you.

01:21:54.619 --> 01:21:59.457
Franklin did this and Franklin did that,
and Franklin did some other damned thing.

01:21:59.582 --> 01:22:02.710
Franklin smote the ground and out sprang

01:22:02.793 --> 01:22:04.504
George Washington,

01:22:04.587 --> 01:22:06.923
fully grown and on his horse.

01:22:07.006 --> 01:22:10.426
Franklin then electrified him
with his miraculous lightning rod

01:22:10.510 --> 01:22:14.138
then the three of them,
Franklin, Washington and the horse,

01:22:14.222 --> 01:22:17.433
conducted the entire revolution
all by themselves.

01:22:20.853 --> 01:22:21.896
I like it.

01:22:23.981 --> 01:22:26.150
I beg your pardon, gentlemen.

01:22:27.276 --> 01:22:31.322
It is indeed an honor
to meet the two greatest men in America.

01:22:31.405 --> 01:22:33.699
Certainly the greatest
within earshot anyway.

01:22:33.783 --> 01:22:35.660
I'm not an idle flatterer, Dr. Franklin.

01:22:35.743 --> 01:22:37.954
My husband admires you both greatly.

01:22:38.162 --> 01:22:39.664
Then we are doubly flattered,

01:22:39.747 --> 01:22:43.125
for we admire very much
that what your husband admires.

01:22:48.256 --> 01:22:49.840
Did you sleep well, madam?

01:22:52.677 --> 01:22:54.595
Well, I mean, did you lie...

01:22:57.139 --> 01:22:58.242
Damn it, you know what I mean.

01:22:58.266 --> 01:22:59.576
Yes, John, we know what you mean.

01:22:59.600 --> 01:23:02.270
Tell us about yourself.
We've heard precious little.

01:23:02.353 --> 01:23:04.355
- What's your first name?
- Martha.

01:23:04.605 --> 01:23:05.648
Martha!

01:23:06.566 --> 01:23:08.693
He might at least have told us that.

01:23:08.776 --> 01:23:10.319
Your husband doesn't say very much.

01:23:10.403 --> 01:23:11.904
Most silent man in congress.

01:23:11.988 --> 01:23:13.924
I have never heard him
utter three sentences together.

01:23:13.948 --> 01:23:15.533
Not every man's a talker, John.

01:23:16.033 --> 01:23:19.829
Yes, it's true, you know.
Tom is not a talker.

01:23:22.540 --> 01:23:26.168
<i>Oh, he never speaks his passions</i>

01:23:26.252 --> 01:23:29.297
<i>he never speaks his views</i>

01:23:29.463 --> 01:23:32.883
<i>whereas other men speak volumes</i>

01:23:32.967 --> 01:23:37.471
<i>the man I love is mute</i>

01:23:37.555 --> 01:23:40.141
<i>in truth I can't recall</i>

01:23:40.224 --> 01:23:43.436
<i>being wooed with words</i>

01:23:43.519 --> 01:23:45.813
<i>at all</i>

01:23:45.896 --> 01:23:49.734
<i>even now</i>

01:23:49.817 --> 01:23:51.319
don't stop, madam.

01:23:51.402 --> 01:23:53.112
No. Tell us, how did he win you?

01:23:53.195 --> 01:23:56.365
And how does he hold on
to a bounty such as you?

01:23:56.449 --> 01:23:59.285
Well, surely you've noticed
that tom is a man of many accomplishments.

01:23:59.368 --> 01:24:00.369
Of course.

01:24:00.453 --> 01:24:03.623
Author, lawyer, statesman,
architect, farmer.

01:24:04.874 --> 01:24:09.003
And still one more that
I hesitate to mention.

01:24:09.086 --> 01:24:11.297
Don't hesitate, madam. Don't hesitate.

01:24:11.380 --> 01:24:14.842
No, tell us.
What else can that redheaded tombstone do?

01:24:17.219 --> 01:24:22.224
<i>He plays the violin</i>

01:24:22.308 --> 01:24:26.562
