<i>we say, "to hell with Great Britain"</i>

01:55:48.484 --> 01:55:53.822
<i>the eagle inside belongs to us</i>

01:56:05.084 --> 01:56:06.644
"and to do all other acts and things

01:56:06.669 --> 01:56:09.004
"which independent states may of right do.

01:56:09.338 --> 01:56:11.465
"And for the support of this declaration,

01:56:11.549 --> 01:56:14.134
"we mutually pledge to
each other our lives,

01:56:14.218 --> 01:56:16.762
"our fortunes and our sacred honor."

01:56:19.390 --> 01:56:21.308
Thank you, Mr. thomson.

01:56:22.059 --> 01:56:25.980
The congress has heard the report
of the declaration committee.

01:56:26.438 --> 01:56:28.732
Are there any here
who wish to offer alterations,

01:56:28.816 --> 01:56:31.652
deletions, amendments to this declaration?

01:56:32.611 --> 01:56:34.113
Mr. president!

01:56:34.738 --> 01:56:36.490
Gentlemen!

01:56:36.574 --> 01:56:39.201
Gentlemen, please!

01:56:40.536 --> 01:56:42.830
Colonel mckean, I saw your hand first.

01:56:42.913 --> 01:56:44.456
Mr. Jefferson,

01:56:44.540 --> 01:56:47.918
it's a funny paper you've written, tom,
but somewhere in it,

01:56:48.002 --> 01:56:51.964
you mention Scottish
and foreign mercenaries sent to destroy us.

01:56:52.756 --> 01:56:54.258
Scottish, tom?

01:56:54.717 --> 01:56:58.053
That is in reference to a highland regiment
which stood against us at Boston.

01:56:59.722 --> 01:57:04.226
It's more likely Germans wearing kilts
to disguise their being there.

01:57:04.351 --> 01:57:09.273
I ask you to remove the word
and avoid giving offense to a good people.

01:57:09.356 --> 01:57:10.858
Mr. Jefferson?

01:57:12.401 --> 01:57:13.861
The reverend...

01:57:14.236 --> 01:57:15.279
Witherspoon.

01:57:15.362 --> 01:57:19.700
Mr. Jefferson,
nowhere do you mention the supreme being.

01:57:19.783 --> 01:57:21.368
Now, surely this was an oversight,

01:57:21.452 --> 01:57:25.956
for how could we hope to achieve a victory
without his help?

01:57:26.040 --> 01:57:28.500
Therefore, I most humbly
suggest the following addition

01:57:28.584 --> 01:57:30.336
to your final sentence.

01:57:30.419 --> 01:57:34.256
"With a firm reliance
on the protection of divine Providence."

01:57:34.590 --> 01:57:35.633
Mr. Jefferson?

01:57:38.761 --> 01:57:39.845
Mr. read.

01:57:41.555 --> 01:57:44.600
Among your charges
against the king, Mr. Jefferson,

01:57:44.683 --> 01:57:48.812
you accuse him of depriving us of
the benefits of trial by jury.

01:57:48.896 --> 01:57:50.272
This is untrue, sir.

01:57:50.356 --> 01:57:53.275
In Delaware, we've always had trial byjury.

01:57:54.193 --> 01:57:56.028
In Massachusetts, we have not.

01:57:56.779 --> 01:58:00.491
Well, then I suggest that the
words "in many cases" be added.

01:58:01.450 --> 01:58:02.951
Mr. Jefferson?

01:58:03.452 --> 01:58:06.664
"In many cases"? Brilliant!

01:58:06.747 --> 01:58:09.291
I suppose every time
you see those three words,

01:58:09.375 --> 01:58:11.543
your puny chest will swell with pride

01:58:11.627 --> 01:58:14.296
over your great historical contribution.

01:58:14.380 --> 01:58:17.716
It's more memorable
than your unprincipled whitewash

01:58:17.800 --> 01:58:19.802
of that race of barbarians!

01:58:19.885 --> 01:58:22.346
Race of barbarians?

01:58:22.429 --> 01:58:23.722
Why, I'll have you...

01:58:24.348 --> 01:58:26.725
Colonel mckean, Mr. read, that's enough!

01:58:29.311 --> 01:58:30.991
- Mr. Hopkins.
- L've no objections, Johnny.

01:58:31.021 --> 01:58:32.731
I'm just trying to get a drink.

01:58:32.815 --> 01:58:35.066
I should've known. Mcnair, get him a rum.

01:58:35.067 --> 01:58:36.707
I should've known. Mcnair, get him a rum.

01:58:40.948 --> 01:58:42.324
Mr. bartlett.

01:58:43.117 --> 01:58:44.284
Mr. Jefferson.

01:58:44.702 --> 01:58:47.496
I beg you to remember
that we still have friends in england.

01:58:47.579 --> 01:58:51.500
I see no purpose in antagonizing
them with such phrases as...

01:58:52.459 --> 01:58:55.212
"Unfeeling brethren" and "enemies at war."

01:58:55.295 --> 01:58:58.632
Our quarrel is with the British king,
not the British people.

01:58:58.716 --> 01:59:00.759
Be sensible, bartlett.

01:59:00.843 --> 01:59:01.844
Remove those phrases,

01:59:01.927 --> 01:59:04.763
and the entire paragraph
becomes meaningless.

01:59:04.847 --> 01:59:08.058
And it so happens that it's one
of the most stirring and poetic

01:59:08.142 --> 01:59:11.478
of any passage
in the entire document. Now...

01:59:11.562 --> 01:59:15.107
We're a congress, Mr. Adams,
not a literary society.

01:59:15.190 --> 01:59:17.943
I ask that the entire
paragraph be stricken.

01:59:18.026 --> 01:59:19.027
Mr. Jefferson?

01:59:21.697 --> 01:59:22.781
Good god.

01:59:22.865 --> 01:59:25.826
Jefferson, when are you going to speak up
for your own work?

01:59:25.909 --> 01:59:28.954
I had hoped
that the work would speak for itself.

01:59:29.538 --> 01:59:30.914
Mr. hancock?

01:59:31.540 --> 01:59:32.916
What is it, Mr. mcnair?

01:59:33.000 --> 01:59:36.462
I can't say I'm very fond of
"the United States of America"

01:59:36.545 --> 01:59:38.046
as a name for a new country.

01:59:40.048 --> 01:59:42.801
I don't care what you're fond of, Mr.
Mcnair.

01:59:42.885 --> 01:59:45.471
You're not a member of this congress!

01:59:48.682 --> 01:59:50.058
Mr. sherman.

01:59:50.601 --> 01:59:53.562
Brother Jefferson, I noted at least

01:59:53.645 --> 01:59:55.773
two distinct and direct references

01:59:55.856 --> 01:59:58.400
to the British parliament
in your declaration.

01:59:58.484 --> 02:00:01.111
Do you think it's wise
to alienate that August body

02:00:01.195 --> 02:00:02.362
in light of our contention

02:00:02.446 --> 02:00:05.073
that they've never
had any authority over us anyway?

02:00:05.157 --> 02:00:07.576
This is a revolution, damn it!

02:00:07.659 --> 02:00:09.745
We're going to have to offend somebody.

02:00:09.828 --> 02:00:11.413
Brother hancock!

02:00:15.834 --> 02:00:17.836
John.John.

02:00:17.920 --> 02:00:20.440
You'll give yourself an attack of
apoplexy if you're not careful.

02:00:20.464 --> 02:00:21.566
Have you heard what they're doing to it?

02:00:21.590 --> 02:00:22.716
- Have you heard?
- I heard.

02:00:22.800 --> 02:00:26.261
And, so far, that's just our friends.
Can you imagine what our enemies will do?

02:00:26.345 --> 02:00:29.097
The word "parliament"
will be removed wherever it occurs.

02:00:29.181 --> 02:00:32.392
They won't be satisfied till they remove
one of the "f's" from Jefferson's name.

02:00:32.476 --> 02:00:35.270
Courage, John. It won't last much longer.

02:00:38.524 --> 02:00:40.025
Mr. Dickinson.

02:00:40.526 --> 02:00:42.569
Mr. Jefferson,

02:00:42.653 --> 02:00:44.530
I have very little interest in your paper,

02:00:44.613 --> 02:00:48.325
as there's no doubt in my mind
that we've all but heard the last of it.

02:00:48.408 --> 02:00:50.994
But I am curious about one thing.

02:00:51.954 --> 02:00:55.374
Why do you refer to king
George as a tyrant?

02:00:57.084 --> 02:00:58.961
Because he is a tyrant.

02:00:59.962 --> 02:01:03.966
I remind you, Mr. Jefferson,
that this tyrant is still your king.

02:01:05.634 --> 02:01:07.886
When a king becomes a tyrant,

02:01:07.970 --> 02:01:11.557
he thereby breaks the contract
binding his subjects to him.

02:01:11.640 --> 02:01:13.267
How so?

02:01:13.350 --> 02:01:15.477
By taking away their rights.

02:01:15.561 --> 02:01:18.522
Rights that came from
him in the first place?

02:01:18.605 --> 02:01:20.315
All except one.

02:01:20.399 --> 02:01:23.110
The right to be free comes from nature.

02:01:23.986 --> 02:01:26.947
And are we not free, Mr. Jefferson?

02:01:29.157 --> 02:01:31.285
Homes entered without warrant.

02:01:31.368 --> 02:01:34.496
Citizens arrested without charge.

02:01:34.580 --> 02:01:37.958
And in many places,
free assembly itself denied.

02:01:38.041 --> 02:01:40.794
No one approves of such things,

02:01:40.878 --> 02:01:43.171
but these are dangerous times.

02:01:43.255 --> 02:01:44.965
Be careful, Mr. Dickinson.

02:01:45.048 --> 02:01:49.136
Those who give up some of their Liberty in
order to obtain a little temporary safety,

02:01:49.219 --> 02:01:51.722
deserve neither Liberty nor safety.

02:01:53.390 --> 02:01:54.766
Mr. Wilson.

02:01:56.268 --> 02:01:59.688
Do we in Pennsylvania
consider king George a tyrant?

02:02:01.023 --> 02:02:03.400
Well, I don't know.

02:02:04.192 --> 02:02:05.319
He...

02:02:07.529 --> 02:02:09.489
No. No, we don't.

02:02:10.240 --> 02:02:11.909
He's not a tyrant.

02:02:12.951 --> 02:02:14.453
In Pennsylvania.

02:02:14.536 --> 02:02:15.954
There you are, Mr. Jefferson.

02:02:16.038 --> 02:02:18.081
Your declaration does not speak for us all.

02:02:18.165 --> 02:02:20.292
I demand the word "tyrant" be removed.

02:02:20.375 --> 02:02:21.375
Very well.

02:02:21.418 --> 02:02:23.587
Just a moment, Mr. thomson.

02:02:23.670 --> 02:02:25.297
I do not consent.

02:02:26.256 --> 02:02:29.885
The king is a tyrant
whether we say so or not.

02:02:31.178 --> 02:02:32.596
We might as well say so.

02:02:32.679 --> 02:02:34.640
But I already scratched it out.

02:02:34.723 --> 02:02:36.683
Then scratch it back in.

02:02:38.435 --> 02:02:41.980
Put it back, Mr. thomson.
The king will remain a tyrant.

02:02:46.068 --> 02:02:47.152
Mr. Hewes.

02:02:47.235 --> 02:02:48.654
Mr. Jefferson.

02:02:48.737 --> 02:02:51.823
Nowhere do you mention
deep-sea fishing rights.

02:02:54.242 --> 02:02:57.245
Good god! Fishing rights!

02:02:58.246 --> 02:03:01.083
How long is this piddling to go on?

02:03:01.166 --> 02:03:04.586
We have been here for three full days.

02:03:04.670 --> 02:03:08.423
We have endured, by my count,
85 separate changes,

02:03:08.507 --> 02:03:11.927
and the removal of close to 400 words.

02:03:12.010 --> 02:03:15.138
Now, would you whip it
and beat it till you break its spirit?

02:03:15.222 --> 02:03:20.894
I tell you that document is a masterful
expression of the American mind!

02:03:26.108 --> 02:03:27.776
If there are no more changes,

02:03:27.859 --> 02:03:31.321
then I can assume the report
of the declaration committee has been...

02:03:31.446 --> 02:03:33.448
Just a moment, Mr. president.

02:03:34.449 --> 02:03:35.701
Look out.

02:03:37.119 --> 02:03:39.663
I wonder if we might prevail
upon Mr. thomson

02:03:39.746 --> 02:03:43.750
to read again a small portion
of Mr. Jefferson's declaration.

02:03:44.835 --> 02:03:47.671
The one beginning
"he has waged cruel war."

02:03:50.632 --> 02:03:52.801
"He has affected... he's combined...

02:03:52.884 --> 02:03:55.345
"He's abdicated... he's plundered...

02:03:55.429 --> 02:03:58.098
"He's constrained...
He's excited... he's incited...

02:03:58.181 --> 02:04:00.600
"He's waged cruel war." Here it is.

02:04:00.684 --> 02:04:03.437
"He's waged cruel war
against human nature itself

02:04:03.520 --> 02:04:06.398
"in the persons
of a distant people who never offended him,

02:04:06.481 --> 02:04:10.402
"captivating and carrying them
into slavery in another hemisphere,

02:04:10.485 --> 02:04:12.070
"determined to keep open a market

02:04:12.154 --> 02:04:14.114
"where men should be bought and sold,

02:04:14.197 --> 02:04:15.277
"he has prostituted his..."

02:04:15.323 --> 02:04:18.410
That will suffice, Mr. thomson.
I thank you, sir.

02:04:18.493 --> 02:04:23.165
Mr. Jefferson, I can't quite make out
what it is you're talking about.

02:04:25.167 --> 02:04:26.960
Slavery, Mr. Rutledge.

02:04:27.044 --> 02:04:28.295
Oh, yes.

02:04:28.378 --> 02:04:31.006
You're referring to us
as slaves of the king.

02:04:31.089 --> 02:04:33.759
No, sir. I'm referring to our slaves.

02:04:33.842 --> 02:04:35.343
Black slaves.

02:04:38.180 --> 02:04:39.639
Black slaves.

02:04:40.849 --> 02:04:43.101
Why didn't you say so, sir?

02:04:43.185 --> 02:04:45.771
Were you trying to hide your meaning?

02:04:46.521 --> 02:04:47.773
No, sir.

02:04:47.856 --> 02:04:50.692
Just another literary license, then.

02:04:51.818 --> 02:04:53.195
If you like.

02:04:54.071 --> 02:04:56.573
I don't like at all, Mr. Jefferson.

02:04:57.616 --> 02:05:01.661
To us, in south Carolina,
black slavery is our peculiar institution,

02:05:01.745 --> 02:05:03.538
and a cherished way of life.

02:05:03.622 --> 02:05:06.458
Nevertheless, we must abolish it.

02:05:06.541 --> 02:05:09.586
Nothing is more certainly written
in the book of fate

02:05:09.669 --> 02:05:11.546
than that these people shall be free.

02:05:11.630 --> 02:05:15.550
I am not concerned with the book of fate
right now, Mr. Jefferson.

02:05:15.634 --> 02:05:18.274
I'm more concerned with what is
written in that little paper there.

02:05:18.345 --> 02:05:22.057
That little paper there
deals with freedom for Americans.

02:05:24.059 --> 02:05:25.393
Oh, really?

02:05:26.853 --> 02:05:28.105
Mr. Adams

02:05:28.855 --> 02:05:33.151
is now calling our black
slaves "Americans."

02:05:33.235 --> 02:05:35.362
- Are they, now?
- Yes, they are.

02:05:35.445 --> 02:05:37.948
They're people and they're here.

02:05:38.031 --> 02:05:39.842
If there's any other requirement,
I've never heard of it.

02:05:39.866 --> 02:05:42.744
They are here, yes, but they are not
people, sir. They are property.

02:05:42.828 --> 02:05:47.040
No, sir. They are people
who are being treated as property.

02:05:47.124 --> 02:05:49.835
I tell you, the rights of human nature

02:05:49.918 --> 02:05:53.505
are deeply wounded
by this infamous practice.

02:05:53.588 --> 02:05:57.509
Then see to your own wounds, Mr. Jefferson,
for you are a practitioner!

02:05:57.592 --> 02:05:59.010
Are you not?

02:06:05.267 --> 02:06:08.103
I have already resolved

02:06:09.104 --> 02:06:10.897
to release my slaves.

02:06:29.291 --> 02:06:30.834
Then I'm sorry,

02:06:31.710 --> 02:06:35.797
for you've also resolved
the ruination of your personal economy.

02:06:35.881 --> 02:06:38.258
Economy. Always economy.

02:06:39.384 --> 02:06:42.387
There's more to this
than a filthy purse string, Rutledge.

02:06:42.470 --> 02:06:44.556
It's an offense against man and god.

02:06:44.639 --> 02:06:48.059
It's a stinking business, Mr. Rutledge.
A stinking business.

02:06:48.143 --> 02:06:50.187
Is it really, Mr. Hopkins?

02:06:50.270 --> 02:06:52.355
Then what is that I smell

02:06:52.439 --> 02:06:54.649
floating down from the north?

02:06:56.193 --> 02:06:58.612
Could that be the aroma of hypocrisy?

02:06:58.695 --> 02:07:02.824
For who holds the other end
of that filthy purse string, Mr. Adams?

02:07:06.286 --> 02:07:11.625
Our northern brethren
feeling a bit tender toward our slaves.

02:07:11.708 --> 02:07:13.627
They don't keep slaves.

02:07:14.169 --> 02:07:15.337
Oh, no.

02:07:16.588 --> 02:07:20.383
But they're willing
to be considerable carriers

02:07:20.467 --> 02:07:22.219
of slaves to others.

02:07:22.969 --> 02:07:24.554
They're willing.

02:07:26.014 --> 02:07:27.641
For the shilling.

02:07:28.141 --> 02:07:30.477
Or haven't you heard, Mr. Adams?

02:07:31.853 --> 02:07:34.439
Clink, clink.

02:07:35.523 --> 02:07:38.109
<i>Molasses to rum</i>

02:07:38.193 --> 02:07:41.029
<i>to slaves</i>

02:07:41.112 --> 02:07:46.701
<i>oh, what a beautiful waltz</i>

02:07:46.785 --> 02:07:49.537
<i>you dance with us</i>

02:07:49.621 --> 02:07:52.040
<i>we dance with you</i>

02:07:52.123 --> 02:07:54.918
<i>in molasses and rum</i>

02:07:55.001 --> 02:08:00.131
<i>and slaves</i>

02:08:00.215 --> 02:08:03.843
<i>who sail the ships out of Boston</i>

02:08:03.927 --> 02:08:07.806
<i>ladened with bibles and rum?</i>

02:08:07.889 --> 02:08:11.518
<i>Who drinks a toast to the Ivory Coast?</i>

02:08:11.601 --> 02:08:15.522
<i>Hail Africa, the slavers have come</i>

02:08:15.605 --> 02:08:19.150
<i>new england with bibles</i>

02:08:19.234 --> 02:08:21.653
<i>and rum</i>

02:08:22.404 --> 02:08:25.240
<i>and it's off with the rum and the bibles</i>

02:08:25.323 --> 02:08:27.826
<i>take on the slaves, clink, clink</i>

02:08:27.909 --> 02:08:31.997
<i>then hail and farewell to the smell</i>

02:08:32.080 --> 02:08:36.251
<i>of the African coast</i>

02:08:39.671 --> 02:08:42.257
<i>molasses to rum</i>

02:08:42.340 --> 02:08:44.718
<i>to slaves</i>

02:08:44.801 --> 02:08:50.348
<i>'tisn't morals, 'tis money that saves</i>

02:08:50.432 --> 02:08:55.687
<i>shall we dance to the sound
of the profitable pound?</i>

02:08:55.770 --> 02:08:58.189
<i>In molasses and rum</i>

02:08:58.273 --> 02:09:03.528
<i>and slaves</i>

02:09:03.611 --> 02:09:07.157
<i>who sail the ships out of Guinea</i>

02:09:07.240 --> 02:09:10.827
<i>ladened with bibles and slaves?</i>

02:09:10.910 --> 02:09:14.622
<i>'Tis Boston can boast
to the west indies coast</i>

02:09:14.706 --> 02:09:18.335
<i>Jamaica, we brung what ye craves</i>

02:09:18.418 --> 02:09:21.963
<i>Antigua, Barbados</i>

02:09:22.047 --> 02:09:25.425
<i>we brung bibles</i>

02:09:25.508 --> 02:09:29.262
<i>and slaves</i>

02:09:29.346 --> 02:09:32.390
gentlemen, you mustn't think
that our northern friends

02:09:32.474 --> 02:09:36.019
see our black slaves
as merely figures in a ledger.

02:09:36.102 --> 02:09:37.395
Oh, no.

02:09:37.479 --> 02:09:41.733
They see them as figures on a block.

02:09:41.816 --> 02:09:44.486
Look at the faces at the
auctions, gentlemen.

02:09:44.569 --> 02:09:47.072
White faces on African wharves.

02:09:47.155 --> 02:09:48.782
Seafaring faces.

02:09:48.865 --> 02:09:50.617
New england faces.

02:09:50.700 --> 02:09:53.078
"Put them in the ships."

02:09:53.161 --> 02:09:55.747
"Cram them in the ships."

02:09:55.830 --> 02:09:59.584
"Stuff them in the ships."

02:09:59.667 --> 02:10:02.962
Hurry, gentlemen. Let the auction begin.

02:10:03.505 --> 02:10:08.593
<i>Ya-ha, ya-ha-ma-cundah</i>

02:10:08.676 --> 02:10:12.472
gentlemen, do you hear?
That's the cry of the auctioneer.

02:10:12.555 --> 02:10:17.644
<i>Ya-ha, ya-ha-ma-cundah</i>

02:10:17.727 --> 02:10:20.146
<i>slaves, gentlemen!</i>

02:10:20.230 --> 02:10:22.607
<i>Black gold!</i>

02:10:22.690 --> 02:10:25.110
<i>Living gold!</i>

02:10:25.193 --> 02:10:28.863
<i>Gold from Angola!</i>

02:10:28.947 --> 02:10:30.824
<i>Guinea, Guinea, Guinea!</i>

02:10:30.907 --> 02:10:33.701
<i>Blackbirds for sale</i>

02:10:33.785 --> 02:10:38.331
<i>ashanti, ibo, ibo, ibo!</i>

02:10:38.415 --> 02:10:41.292
<i>Blackbirds for sale</i>

02:10:41.376 --> 02:10:45.296
<i>handle them!</i>

02:10:45.713 --> 02:10:49.134
<i>Fondle them!</i>

02:10:49.217 --> 02:10:52.303
<i>But don't finger them!</i>

02:10:52.387 --> 02:10:54.597
<i>They're prime</i>

02:10:54.681 --> 02:10:57.350
<i>they're prime</i>

02:10:57.434 --> 02:11:04.149
<i>ya-ha, ya-ha-ma-cundah</i>

02:11:04.732 --> 02:11:07.944
for the love of god, Mr. Rutledge, please.

02:11:16.995 --> 02:11:19.914
<i>Molasses to rum</i>

02:11:19.998 --> 02:11:23.418
<i>to slaves</i>

02:11:23.501 --> 02:11:28.506
<i>who sail the ships back to Boston</i>

02:11:28.590 --> 02:11:30.967
<i>ladened with gold</i>

02:11:31.050 --> 02:11:34.179
<i>see it gleam</i>

02:11:34.262 --> 02:11:38.975
<i>whose fortunes are made
in the triangle trade</i>

02:11:39.058 --> 02:11:43.480
<i>hail slavery, the new england dream</i>

02:11:43.563 --> 02:11:46.107
<i>Mr. Adams, I give you a toast</i>

02:11:47.150 --> 02:11:49.402
<i>hail, Boston</i>

02:11:49.486 --> 02:11:52.071
<i>hail, Charleston</i>

02:11:53.615 --> 02:12:00.622
<i>who stinketh the most?</i>

02:12:08.880 --> 02:12:11.299
Mr. Rutledge, please!

02:12:14.093 --> 02:12:15.428
Mr. Hewes.

02:12:18.890 --> 02:12:20.141
Dr. hall.

02:12:30.985 --> 02:12:33.571
Don't worry, John. They'll be back.

02:12:33.655 --> 02:12:36.282
Aye, to vote us down.

02:12:42.956 --> 02:12:44.958
Adams! Franklin!

02:12:46.501 --> 02:12:48.419
It's done. I have it.

02:12:48.503 --> 02:12:50.964
And the Maryland assembly's approved it.

02:12:51.047 --> 02:12:56.177
I told them about one of the
greatest military engagements in history

02:12:56.261 --> 02:12:58.388
against a flock of...

02:13:01.683 --> 02:13:03.142
What's wrong?

02:13:04.727 --> 02:13:07.730
- I thought...
- You'll have to forgive them, Mr. chase.

02:13:07.814 --> 02:13:10.483
They just suffered a slight setback.

02:13:10.567 --> 02:13:13.278
And after all, "what is a man profited

02:13:13.361 --> 02:13:17.615
"if he shall gain Maryland
and lose the entire south?"

02:13:18.825 --> 02:13:21.703
Matthew, chapter 16, verse 26.

02:13:23.454 --> 02:13:24.664
Mcnair.

02:13:25.331 --> 02:13:27.166
I know. The flies.

02:13:27.250 --> 02:13:28.293
No.

02:13:29.210 --> 02:13:30.461
The rum.

02:13:35.091 --> 02:13:37.885
Well, what are we all sitting around for?

02:13:39.262 --> 02:13:40.972
We're wasting time. Precious time.

02:13:41.055 --> 02:13:43.141
Thomas, I want you
to ride down into Delaware

02:13:43.224 --> 02:13:44.851
and fetch back Caesar Rodney.

02:13:44.934 --> 02:13:48.271
John, are you mad?
It's 80 miles, and he's a dying man.

02:13:48.354 --> 02:13:50.398
No, he's a patriot.

02:13:50.481 --> 02:13:52.859
John, what good will it do?
The south's done us in.

02:13:52.942 --> 02:13:54.569
And suppose they change their minds?

02:13:54.652 --> 02:13:57.155
Can we get Delaware without Rodney?

02:13:59.907 --> 02:14:02.952
God! What a bastardly bunch we are.

02:14:05.496 --> 02:14:08.750
- Stephen, I want you to...
- L'm going to the tavern, Johnny.

02:14:08.833 --> 02:14:12.378
If there's anything I can do for you there,
let me know.

02:14:13.296 --> 02:14:14.464
Chase.

02:14:15.340 --> 02:14:16.424
Bartlett!

02:14:16.507 --> 02:14:20.094
What's the use, John?
The vote's tomorrow morning.

02:14:20.178 --> 02:14:22.597
There's less than a full day left.

02:14:25.975 --> 02:14:27.518
Roger.

02:14:27.602 --> 02:14:30.104
Face facts, John. It's finished.

02:14:32.857 --> 02:14:34.442
I'm sorry, John.

02:14:42.825 --> 02:14:44.786
We have no choice, John.

02:14:45.953 --> 02:14:47.789
The slavery clause has got to go.

02:14:51.042 --> 02:14:52.460
Franklin, what are you saying?

02:14:52.960 --> 02:14:54.754
It's a luxury we can't afford.

02:14:55.880 --> 02:14:57.131
A luxury?

02:14:59.550 --> 02:15:03.304
A half million souls in chains,

02:15:03.388 --> 02:15:06.391
and Dr. Franklin calls it a luxury.

02:15:07.517 --> 02:15:09.394
Maybe you should've
walked out with the south.

02:15:09.936 --> 02:15:11.896
You forget yourself, sir.

02:15:11.979 --> 02:15:15.149
I founded the first anti-slavery society
on this continent.

02:15:15.608 --> 02:15:18.903
Don't wave your credentials at me.
Perhaps it's time you had them renewed.

02:15:19.529 --> 02:15:22.573
The issue here is independence.

02:15:22.657 --> 02:15:25.451
Perhaps you've forgotten that fact,
but I have not.

02:15:25.535 --> 02:15:29.080
How dare you jeopardize our cause

02:15:29.163 --> 02:15:31.082
when we've come so far!

02:15:32.709 --> 02:15:34.043
These men,

02:15:35.336 --> 02:15:37.588
no matter how much
we may disagree with them,

02:15:37.672 --> 02:15:41.092
are not ribbon clerks to be ordered about.

02:15:41.175 --> 02:15:44.387
They're proud, accomplished men.
The cream of their colonies.

02:15:44.470 --> 02:15:47.473
And whether you like it or not,
they and the people they represent

02:15:47.557 --> 02:15:51.436
will be part of this new nation
you hope to create.

02:15:51.519 --> 02:15:54.731
Now either learn how to live with them
or pack up and go home.

02:16:00.361 --> 02:16:03.448
In any case,
stop acting like a Boston fishwife.

02:16:17.545 --> 02:16:20.423
Good god. What's happened to me?

02:16:20.506 --> 02:16:23.801
John Adams. The great John Adams.

02:16:24.302 --> 02:16:25.845
What have I come to?

02:16:25.928 --> 02:16:27.805
Law practice down the pipe.

02:16:27.889 --> 02:16:30.016
Farm mortgaged to the hilt.

02:16:30.099 --> 02:16:33.227
At a stage in life when other men prosper,

02:16:33.311 --> 02:16:35.938
I'm reduced to living in Philadelphia.

02:16:37.982 --> 02:16:39.441
Philadelphia.

02:16:48.825 --> 02:16:51.412
Abigail, what am I going to do?

02:16:51.495 --> 02:16:52.746
<i>Do, John?</i>

02:16:54.081 --> 02:16:55.750
I need your help.

02:16:56.416 --> 02:16:59.045
<i>You don't usually ask my advice.</i>

02:16:59.128 --> 02:17:02.548
Yes, well, there doesn't appear
to be anyone else right now.

02:17:02.632 --> 02:17:04.759
<i>Very well, John. What is it?</i>

02:17:05.510 --> 02:17:08.930
The entire south
has just walked out of this congress,

02:17:09.555 --> 02:17:13.518
George Washington
is on the verge of total annihilation,

02:17:13.601 --> 02:17:16.603
and the precious cause for which I
have labored these several years

02:17:16.687 --> 02:17:18.439
has come to nothing.

02:17:20.398 --> 02:17:23.861
And it seems
that I'm obnoxious and disliked.

02:17:23.945 --> 02:17:25.571
<i>Nonsense, John.</i>

02:17:26.322 --> 02:17:28.782
That I am unwilling to face reality.

02:17:28.866 --> 02:17:30.993
<i>Foolishness, John.</i>

02:17:31.076 --> 02:17:32.787
That I'm pigheaded.

02:17:33.412 --> 02:17:35.206
<i>Well, there you have me, John.</i>

02:17:35.289 --> 02:17:37.333
<i>I'm afraid you are pigheaded.</i>

02:17:41.254 --> 02:17:42.588
Well, yes.

02:17:45.174 --> 02:17:46.467
Abby.

02:17:47.927 --> 02:17:50.638
Has it been any kind of a life for you?

02:17:51.513 --> 02:17:53.766
God knows I haven't given you very much.

02:17:54.642 --> 02:17:56.519
I never asked for more.

02:17:57.311 --> 02:17:59.230
After all, I am Mrs. John Adams.

02:17:59.313 --> 02:18:01.858
That's quite a lot for one lifetime.

02:18:04.151 --> 02:18:05.570
Is it, Abby?

02:18:06.361 --> 02:18:08.364
Well, think of it, John.
To be married to the man

02:18:08.447 --> 02:18:11.534
who is always the first
in line to be hanged...

02:18:15.871 --> 02:18:17.790
Yes. The agitator.

02:18:20.334 --> 02:18:21.669
Why, Abby?

02:18:23.754 --> 02:18:26.173
You must tell me what it is. I...

02:18:26.841 --> 02:18:30.093
Well, I have always been dissatisfied.
I know that.

02:18:31.596 --> 02:18:36.183
But lately, i
find that I reek of discontentment.

02:18:36.267 --> 02:18:39.603
It fills my throat and it floods my brain.

02:18:43.941 --> 02:18:46.861
Sometimes I fear there
is no longer a dream,

02:18:48.154 --> 02:18:50.281
but only the discontentment.

02:18:52.407 --> 02:18:53.825
Oh, John.

02:18:56.245 --> 02:18:59.248
Can you really know so
little about yourself?

02:19:00.833 --> 02:19:02.126
Can you think so little of me

02:19:02.209 --> 02:19:05.588
that you'd believe
I'd marry the man you've described?

02:19:07.757 --> 02:19:11.343
Have you forgotten
what you used to say to me? I haven't.

02:19:12.719 --> 02:19:14.805
"Commitment, Abby.

02:19:15.889 --> 02:19:17.266
"Commitment.

02:19:18.726 --> 02:19:22.730
"There are only two creatures of value
on the face of this earth.

02:19:23.814 --> 02:19:25.983
"Those with a commitment,

02:19:26.066 --> 02:19:29.236
"and those who require
the commitment of others."

02:19:31.405 --> 02:19:33.240
Do you remember, John?

02:19:35.493 --> 02:19:37.077
Yes, I remember.

02:19:37.702 --> 02:19:39.621
Mr. Adams!

02:19:41.248 --> 02:19:43.584
Are you up there, Mr. Adams?

02:19:44.251 --> 02:19:45.920
What do you want?

02:19:46.337 --> 02:19:50.132
There's a delivery down here for you.

02:19:50.216 --> 02:19:51.592
What is it?

02:19:53.469 --> 02:19:55.680
Where did it come from? Who sent it?

02:20:01.936 --> 02:20:06.565
<i>Compliments of
the Concord ladies' coffee club</i>

02:20:06.649 --> 02:20:11.529
<i>and the sisterhood of the truro synagogue</i>

02:20:11.612 --> 02:20:16.492
<i>and the Friday evening
baptist sewing circle</i>

02:20:16.575 --> 02:20:21.539
<i>and the holy Christian sisters of St.
Claire</i>

02:20:21.622 --> 02:20:25.626
<i>all for you</i>

02:20:25.710 --> 02:20:28.838
<i>John</i>

02:20:28.921 --> 02:20:34.343
<i>I am as I ever was</i>

02:20:34.427 --> 02:20:39.306
<i>and ever shall be</i>

02:20:39.390 --> 02:20:44.895
<i>yours, yours, yours</i>

02:20:44.979 --> 02:20:47.606
<i>yours</i>

02:20:47.690 --> 02:20:50.943
Abigail, what's in these kegs?

02:20:51.444 --> 02:20:57.992
<i>Saltpeter, John</i>

02:21:05.833 --> 02:21:07.001
mcnair!

02:21:07.877 --> 02:21:11.088
Mcnair, go out and buy every damned pin
you can find in Philadelphia.

02:21:11.172 --> 02:21:12.923
Pin? What sort of pin?

02:21:13.007 --> 02:21:15.926
Well, I don't know.
Whatever the ladies use for their sewing.

02:21:16.010 --> 02:21:19.430
Franklin, Jefferson,
what are you all sitting around for?

02:21:19.513 --> 02:21:21.223
Didn't you hear a word I said before?

02:21:21.307 --> 02:21:23.059
Never mind about that.

02:21:23.142 --> 02:21:24.769
Now, here's what I want you to do.

02:21:24.852 --> 02:21:27.063
John, I'm not even speaking to you.

02:21:27.146 --> 02:21:29.899
It's too late for that, damn it.
There's work to be done.

02:21:29.982 --> 02:21:31.817
Jefferson, go find Rutledge.

02:21:31.901 --> 02:21:33.861
Don't come back
until you've worn him down.

02:21:33.944 --> 02:21:35.863
Now, you're both Southern aristocrats.

02:21:35.946 --> 02:21:38.032
If he'll listen to anybody,
he'll listen to you.

02:21:38.115 --> 02:21:40.034
Franklin, out of that chair!

02:21:40.117 --> 02:21:42.745
What good is the south
if you can't deliver Pennsylvania?

02:21:42.828 --> 02:21:44.413
Talk to Wilson.

02:21:44.497 --> 02:21:45.748
Get him away from Dickinson.

02:21:45.831 --> 02:21:49.001
That's the only way to do it.
Go on, now, both of you.

02:21:49.210 --> 02:21:51.712
- John...
- Time's running out, damn it.

02:21:52.588 --> 02:21:53.881
Now move.

02:21:57.259 --> 02:21:58.803
I'm still from Massachusetts, John.

02:22:00.763 --> 02:22:02.681
You know where I stand.

02:22:03.140 --> 02:22:04.475
I'll do whatever you say.

02:22:08.020 --> 02:22:09.188
No.

02:22:10.481 --> 02:22:13.067
No, you're the president of congress.

02:22:14.318 --> 02:22:17.029
You're a fair man, hancock. Stay that way.

02:22:39.301 --> 02:22:42.763
Tell me, Mr. thomson, out of curiosity,

02:22:43.472 --> 02:22:47.059
do you stand with Mr. Dickinson,
or do you stand with me?

02:22:49.019 --> 02:22:51.021
I stand with the general.

02:22:52.940 --> 02:22:57.236
Well, lately,
I've had the oddest feeling that he's been

02:22:57.319 --> 02:22:58.821
writing to me.

02:23:02.908 --> 02:23:05.911
<i>I have been in expectation</i>

02:23:05.995 --> 02:23:09.206
<i>of receiving a reply</i>

02:23:09.290 --> 02:23:15.462
<i>on the subject of my last 15 dispatches</i>

02:23:16.630 --> 02:23:21.886
<i>ls anybody there?</i>

02:23:23.053 --> 02:23:28.642
<i>Does anybody care?</i>

02:23:29.810 --> 02:23:35.232
<i>Does anybody care?</i>

02:23:37.401 --> 02:23:39.820
"Your humble and obedient..."

02:24:13.062 --> 02:24:14.730
"Ls anybody there?

02:24:18.400 --> 02:24:20.653
"Does anybody care?"

02:24:24.323 --> 02:24:30.829
<i>Does anybody see what I see?</i>

02:24:34.541 --> 02:24:36.877
<i>They want me to quit</i>

02:24:37.878 --> 02:24:42.216
<i>they say, "John, give up the fight"</i>

02:24:42.299 --> 02:24:45.386
<i>still to england, I say</i>

02:24:45.469 --> 02:24:48.889
<i>good night, forever, good night!</i>

02:24:49.890 --> 02:24:54.561
<i>For I have crossed the rubicon</i>

02:24:54.645 --> 02:24:57.439
<i>let the bridge be burned behind me</i>

02:24:57.523 --> 02:24:59.817
<i>come what may</i>

02:24:59.900 --> 02:25:01.986
<i>come what may</i>

02:25:02.069 --> 02:25:03.153
commitment!

02:25:03.570 --> 02:25:07.825
<i>The croakers all say we'll rue the day</i>

02:25:07.908 --> 02:25:13.163
<i>there'll be hell to pay in fiery purgatory</i>

02:25:13.247 --> 02:25:17.001
<i>through all the gloom,
through all the gloom</i>

02:25:17.084 --> 02:25:21.046
<i>I can see the rays of ravishing light</i>

02:25:21.130 --> 02:25:23.465
<i>and qioty</i>

02:25:23.924 --> 02:25:25.926
<i>ls anybody there?</i>

02:25:27.177 --> 02:25:29.596
<i>Does anybody care?</i>

02:25:30.306 --> 02:25:33.350
<i>Does anybody see what I see?</i>

02:25:34.476 --> 02:25:36.437
<i>I see fireworks</i>

02:25:37.146 --> 02:25:40.482
<i>I see the pageant and pomp and parade</i>

02:25:40.566 --> 02:25:43.027
<i>I hear the bells ringing out</i>

02:25:43.110 --> 02:25:46.238
<i>I hear the cannons roar</i>

02:25:46.322 --> 02:25:48.866
<i>I see Americans</i>

02:25:48.949 --> 02:25:52.369
<i>all Americans free</i>

02:25:52.453 --> 02:25:55.706
<i>forevermore</i>

02:26:08.635 --> 02:26:14.183
<i>how quiet, how quiet the chamber is</i>

02:26:15.476 --> 02:26:22.316
<i>how silent, how silent the chamber is</i>

02:26:26.070 --> 02:26:31.450
<i>ls anybody there?</i>

02:26:32.826 --> 02:26:37.998
<i>Does anybody care?</i>

02:26:39.875 --> 02:26:45.214
<i>Does anybody see what I see?</i>

02:26:46.840 --> 02:26:48.384
Yes, Mr. Adams.

02:26:50.386 --> 02:26:51.553
I do.

02:26:55.349 --> 02:26:56.642
Dr. hall.

02:26:57.434 --> 02:26:59.520
I didn't know anyone was...

02:27:00.646 --> 02:27:02.773
I'm sorry if I startled you.

02:27:03.649 --> 02:27:05.275
I couldn't sleep.

02:27:06.318 --> 02:27:09.738
And in trying to resolve my dilemma,

02:27:09.822 --> 02:27:12.741
I remembered something I'd once read.

02:27:12.825 --> 02:27:16.620
That a representative
owes the people not only his industry,

02:27:16.703 --> 02:27:19.206
but his judgment.

02:27:19.289 --> 02:27:22.751
And he betrays them
if he sacrifices it to their opinion.

02:27:25.879 --> 02:27:28.257
That was written by Edmund Burke,

02:27:29.800 --> 02:27:32.302
a member of the British parliament.

02:28:01.248 --> 02:28:03.167
Good night, Mr. Adams.

02:28:03.250 --> 02:28:04.585
Good night.

02:28:15.679 --> 02:28:17.389
<i>It's never been done before.</i>

02:28:17.473 --> 02:28:20.118
<i>No colony has ever broken from the
parent stem in the history of the world.</i>

02:28:20.142 --> 02:28:22.811
<i>If you have grievances,
and I'm sure you have,</i>

02:28:22.895 --> 02:28:26.023
<i>our present system must provide
a gentler means of redressing them</i>

02:28:26.106 --> 02:28:28.233
<i>- short of revolution.
- We've spawned a new race here.</i>

02:28:28.317 --> 02:28:29.526
<i>Rougher, simpler,</i>

02:28:29.610 --> 02:28:32.321
<i>more violent, more
enterprising, less refined.</i>

02:28:32.404 --> 02:28:35.866
<i>"My quartermaster has no food,
no arms, no ammunition,</i>

02:28:35.949 --> 02:28:38.660
<i>"and my troops are in a
state of near mutiny."</i>

02:28:38.744 --> 02:28:40.638
<i>- No army, no Navy...
- "I pray god some relief arrives</i>

02:28:40.662 --> 02:28:43.099
<i>- "before the armada, but fear it will not."
- No arms, no ammunition,</i>

02:28:43.123 --> 02:28:46.043
<i>- no treasury, no friends.
- And when they hang you, Mr. Adams,</i>

02:28:46.126 --> 02:28:48.629
<i>I do hope you'll put in a good word
for the rest of us.</i>

02:28:48.712 --> 02:28:51.840
<i>England closing in, cutting off our air.</i>

02:28:51.924 --> 02:28:52.925
<i>There's no time!</i>

02:28:53.008 --> 02:28:56.178
<i>To place before mankind
the common sense of the subject...</i>

02:28:56.261 --> 02:28:58.555
<i>The issue here is independence.</i>

02:28:58.639 --> 02:29:00.575
<i>Perhaps you've lost sight of that fact,
but I have not.</i>

02:29:00.599 --> 02:29:02.285
<i>"We mutually pledge to each other our lives</i>

02:29:02.309 --> 02:29:05.312
<i>"our fortunes and our sacred honor."</i>

02:29:06.063 --> 02:29:09.066
<i>Can you really know so
little about yourself?</i>

02:29:14.112 --> 02:29:15.447
Very well.

02:29:17.366 --> 02:29:21.537
The congress will now vote
on Virginia's resolution on independence.

02:29:29.545 --> 02:29:30.796
Thank you for coming, Caesar.

02:29:31.755 --> 02:29:33.507
God bless you, sir.

02:29:39.012 --> 02:29:41.181
The secretary will call the roll.

02:29:41.265 --> 02:29:44.226
And I remind you, gentlemen,

02:29:44.309 --> 02:29:46.478
that a single "nay" vote

02:29:47.604 --> 02:29:49.523
will defeat the motion.

02:29:50.816 --> 02:29:52.192
Mr. thomson.

02:29:57.364 --> 02:29:58.865
New Hampshire?

02:29:59.241 --> 02:30:00.409
New Hampshire says yea.

02:30:00.492 --> 02:30:02.995
New Hampshire says yea. Massachusetts?

02:30:03.078 --> 02:30:04.246
Massachusetts says yea.

02:30:04.329 --> 02:30:06.707
Massachusetts says yea. Rhode Island?

02:30:06.790 --> 02:30:08.125
Rhode Island says yea.

02:30:08.208 --> 02:30:10.752
Rhode Island says yea. Connecticut?

02:30:10.836 --> 02:30:12.045
Connecticut says yea.

02:30:12.129 --> 02:30:14.923
Connecticut says yea. New York?

02:30:15.007 --> 02:30:18.260
Mr. secretary,
New York abstains courteously.

02:30:18.343 --> 02:30:20.679
- New York abstains.
- Courteously.

02:30:22.097 --> 02:30:23.640
New Jersey?

02:30:23.724 --> 02:30:25.017
New Jersey says yea.

02:30:25.100 --> 02:30:27.686
New Jersey says yea. Pennsylvania?

02:30:29.688 --> 02:30:31.857
Mr. secretary, Pennsylvania is not ready.

02:30:31.940 --> 02:30:34.151
Please come back to us later.

02:30:34.234 --> 02:30:36.486
Pennsylvania passes. Delaware?

02:30:36.570 --> 02:30:37.613
Just a moment.

02:30:38.655 --> 02:30:41.908
Delaware, by majority vote...

02:30:42.492 --> 02:30:45.162
- Aye.
- Says yea.

02:30:45.245 --> 02:30:48.206
Delaware says yea. Maryland?

02:30:48.290 --> 02:30:49.499
Maryland says yea.

02:30:49.583 --> 02:30:51.209
Maryland says yea. Virginia?

02:30:51.293 --> 02:30:52.336
Virginia says yea.

02:30:52.419 --> 02:30:54.504
Virginia says yea. North Carolina?

02:30:54.588 --> 02:30:57.341
North Carolina yields to south Carolina.

02:30:58.592 --> 02:30:59.593
South Carolina?

02:31:00.594 --> 02:31:02.262
Well, Mr. Adams?

02:31:03.388 --> 02:31:04.681
Well, Mr. Rutledge.

02:31:07.768 --> 02:31:09.102
Mr. Adams,

02:31:11.605 --> 02:31:15.567
you must believe
that I will do what I promised to do.

02:31:22.324 --> 02:31:23.909
What is it you want, Rutledge?

02:31:23.992 --> 02:31:27.621
Remove the offending passage
from your declaration.

02:31:27.996 --> 02:31:30.123
If we did that, we would be guilty

02:31:30.207 --> 02:31:33.126
of what we ourselves are rebelling against.

02:31:35.087 --> 02:31:37.297
Nevertheless remove it,

02:31:38.048 --> 02:31:41.134
or south Carolina will bury now and forever

02:31:41.218 --> 02:31:43.303
your dream of independence.

02:31:44.346 --> 02:31:47.808
John, I beg you, consider
what you're doing.

02:31:54.773 --> 02:31:56.400
Mark me, Franklin,

02:31:57.526 --> 02:31:59.986
if we give in on this issue,

02:32:00.070 --> 02:32:02.572
posterity will never forgive us.

02:32:02.656 --> 02:32:04.741
That's probably true,
but we won't hear a thing.

02:32:04.825 --> 02:32:06.910
We'll be long gone.

02:32:06.993 --> 02:32:11.331
Besides, what will posterity think we were?
Demigods?

02:32:11.998 --> 02:32:13.583
We're men, no more, no less,

02:32:13.667 --> 02:32:16.545
trying to get a nation started
against greater odds

02:32:16.628 --> 02:32:19.506
than a more generous god
would have allowed.

02:32:20.132 --> 02:32:23.385
First things first, John.
Independence. America.

02:32:23.468 --> 02:32:25.929
If we don't secure that,

02:32:26.012 --> 02:32:28.515
what difference will the rest make?

02:32:34.646 --> 02:32:36.648
Jefferson, say something.

02:32:39.109 --> 02:32:41.111
What else is there to do?

02:32:42.028 --> 02:32:44.781
Well, man, you're the one that wrote it.

02:32:45.657 --> 02:32:48.785
I wrote all of it, Mr. Adams.

02:33:10.056 --> 02:33:11.266
There.

02:33:11.349 --> 02:33:14.120
There it is, Rutledge. You have your
slavery. Little good may it do you.

02:33:14.144 --> 02:33:16.062
You now vote, damn you!

02:33:17.647 --> 02:33:21.443
Mr. president,
the fair colony of south Carolina

02:33:22.736 --> 02:33:24.321
says yea.

02:33:24.404 --> 02:33:25.906
South Carolina says yea.

02:33:25.989 --> 02:33:27.491
North Carolina says yea.

02:33:27.574 --> 02:33:29.534
North Carolina says yea.

02:33:31.077 --> 02:33:32.162
Georgia?

02:33:32.245 --> 02:33:33.622
Georgia says yea.

02:33:33.705 --> 02:33:35.248
Georgia says yea.

02:33:36.583 --> 02:33:38.376
Pennsylvania, second call.

02:33:40.420 --> 02:33:42.255
Mr. president,

02:33:42.339 --> 02:33:45.509
Pennsylvania regrets
all of the inconvenience

02:33:45.592 --> 02:33:50.639
that such distinguished men
as Adams, Franklin and Jefferson

02:33:50.722 --> 02:33:52.557
were put to just now.

02:33:52.641 --> 02:33:54.434
They might've kept their document intact

02:33:54.518 --> 02:33:57.103
for all the difference it will make.

02:33:57.187 --> 02:33:58.814
Mr. president,

02:33:59.231 --> 02:34:00.607
Pennsylvania says...

02:34:00.690 --> 02:34:01.775
Just a moment.

02:34:03.443 --> 02:34:05.445
I ask the delegation to be polled.

02:34:06.196 --> 02:34:08.323
Dr. Franklin, don't be absurd.

02:34:08.782 --> 02:34:11.785
A poll, Mr. president.
It's a proper request.

02:34:12.035 --> 02:34:13.203
Yes, it is.

02:34:13.286 --> 02:34:15.580
Poll the delegation, Mr. thomson.

02:34:15.664 --> 02:34:17.374
Dr. Benjamin Franklin.

02:34:17.457 --> 02:34:18.500
Yea.

02:34:18.583 --> 02:34:20.544
Mr. John Dickinson.

02:34:20.627 --> 02:34:22.003
Nay.

02:34:22.087 --> 02:34:23.713
Mr. James Wilson.

02:34:26.925 --> 02:34:28.385
Judge Wilson?

02:34:31.555 --> 02:34:34.140
There it is, Mr. Wilson.
It's all up to you now.

02:34:34.224 --> 02:34:35.904
The whole question
of American independence

02:34:35.976 --> 02:34:38.562
rests squarely on your shoulders.

02:34:38.645 --> 02:34:42.190
An entirely new nation
ready to be born or to die at birth,

02:34:42.274 --> 02:34:43.984
all on your say-so.

02:34:45.110 --> 02:34:47.320
Which will it be, Mr. Wilson?

02:34:47.779 --> 02:34:51.324
Every mapmaker in the world
is waiting for your decision.

02:34:51.950 --> 02:34:55.078
Come now, James. Nothing has changed.

02:34:55.161 --> 02:34:57.914
We mustn't let Dr. Franklin
create one of his confusions.

02:34:57.998 --> 02:34:59.875
The question is clear.

02:35:00.375 --> 02:35:03.920
Most questions are clear
when someone else has to decide them.

02:35:04.004 --> 02:35:05.463
It would be a pity for a man

02:35:05.547 --> 02:35:08.091
who's handed down hundreds
of wise decisions

02:35:08.174 --> 02:35:10.010
from the bench

02:35:10.093 --> 02:35:13.263
to be remembered only
for the one unwise decision

02:35:13.346 --> 02:35:15.140
he made in congress.

02:35:16.600 --> 02:35:19.561
James, you're keeping everybody waiting.

02:35:19.644 --> 02:35:21.688
The secretary has called for your vote.

02:35:22.564 --> 02:35:23.773
Please.

02:35:25.108 --> 02:35:28.695
Don't push me, John.
I know what you want me to do.

02:35:31.448 --> 02:35:34.242
But Mr. Adams is correct about one thing.

02:35:36.745 --> 02:35:39.497
I'm the one who'll be remembered for it.

02:35:39.789 --> 02:35:40.874
What do you mean?

02:35:46.588 --> 02:35:48.798
I'm different from you, John.

02:35:49.633 --> 02:35:52.385
I'm different from most of the men here.

02:35:53.345 --> 02:35:55.555
I don't want to be remembered.

02:35:56.806 --> 02:35:58.767
I just don't want the

02:35:59.601 --> 02:36:01.144
responsibility.

02:36:02.270 --> 02:36:04.773
Yes, well, whether you
want it or not, James,

02:36:04.856 --> 02:36:07.108
there's no way of avoiding it.

02:36:07.192 --> 02:36:09.069
Not necessarily, John.

02:36:09.736 --> 02:36:11.738
If I go with them,

02:36:11.821 --> 02:36:14.074
I'll just be one among dozens.

02:36:15.909 --> 02:36:19.162
No one will ever remember
the name of James Wilson.

02:36:20.538 --> 02:36:22.415
But if I vote with you,

02:36:23.917 --> 02:36:27.253
I'll be the man
who prevented American independence.

02:36:30.090 --> 02:36:31.716
I'm sorry, John.

02:36:33.134 --> 02:36:35.428
I just didn't bargain for that.

02:36:37.013 --> 02:36:40.433
And is that how new nations are formed?

02:36:41.851 --> 02:36:44.354
By a nonentity trying to preserve

02:36:44.437 --> 02:36:47.732
the anonymity he so richly deserves?

02:36:48.608 --> 02:36:52.028
Revolutions come into this world
like bastard children, Mr. Dickinson.

02:36:52.112 --> 02:36:54.698
Half improvised and half compromised.

02:36:54.781 --> 02:36:57.200
Our side has provided the compromise.

02:36:57.283 --> 02:36:59.953
Now judge Wilson is supplying the rest.

02:37:04.124 --> 02:37:05.291
James.

02:37:06.835 --> 02:37:08.461
I'm sorry, John.

02:37:09.504 --> 02:37:10.714
My vote

02:37:11.923 --> 02:37:13.174
is yea.

02:37:13.967 --> 02:37:15.802
Mr. secretary, Pennsylvania says yea.

02:37:18.638 --> 02:37:22.267
The count being 12 to none

02:37:24.394 --> 02:37:25.729
with one abstention,

02:37:26.104 --> 02:37:28.314
the resolution on independence

02:37:30.275 --> 02:37:31.651
is adopted.

02:37:33.111 --> 02:37:34.446
It's done.

02:37:37.782 --> 02:37:39.117
It's done.

02:37:41.828 --> 02:37:43.204
Mr. thomson,

02:37:44.164 --> 02:37:45.749
is the declaration ready to be signed?

02:37:45.832 --> 02:37:47.459
It is.

02:37:47.542 --> 02:37:49.502
Then I suggest we do so.

02:37:51.337 --> 02:37:53.006
And the chair further proposes,

02:37:53.089 --> 02:37:55.800
for our mutual security and protection,

02:37:57.719 --> 02:37:59.679
that no man be allowed
to sit in this congress

02:37:59.763 --> 02:38:02.057
without attaching his name to it.

02:38:05.101 --> 02:38:07.979
I'm sorry, Mr. president.

02:38:09.439 --> 02:38:13.735
I cannot, in good conscience,
sign such a document.

02:38:15.361 --> 02:38:19.616
I will never stop hoping for our
eventual reconciliation with england.

02:38:21.284 --> 02:38:23.453
But because,

02:38:24.704 --> 02:38:26.206
in my own way,

02:38:27.207 --> 02:38:30.710
I regard America no less
than does Mr. Adams,

02:38:32.796 --> 02:38:36.674
I will join the army and
fight in her defense

02:38:38.218 --> 02:38:41.304
even though I believe
that fight to be hopeless.

02:38:46.976 --> 02:38:48.728
Goodbye, gentlemen.

02:38:50.814 --> 02:38:52.982
Gentlemen of the congress,

02:38:53.066 --> 02:38:55.401
I say yea, John Dickinson.

02:39:07.122 --> 02:39:08.456
Very well.

02:39:09.415 --> 02:39:11.167
Are there any objections to the declaration

02:39:11.251 --> 02:39:12.836
being approved as it now stands?

02:39:13.336 --> 02:39:14.462
I have one, Mr. hancock.

02:39:15.338 --> 02:39:16.881
You, Mr. Adams?

02:39:17.423 --> 02:39:19.509
Yes. Mr. Jefferson,

02:39:19.968 --> 02:39:24.097
it so happens that the
word is "unalienable,"

02:39:24.180 --> 02:39:25.974
not "inalienable."

02:39:27.684 --> 02:39:31.771
I'm sorry, Mr. Adams,
but "inalienable" is correct.

02:39:33.314 --> 02:39:36.484
I happen to be a Harvard graduate,
Mr. Jefferson.

02:39:39.612 --> 02:39:42.323
I attended William and Mary, Mr. Adams.

02:39:43.741 --> 02:39:44.993
Gentlemen, please!

02:39:45.076 --> 02:39:48.580
Mr. Jefferson,
will you yield to Mr. Adams' request?

02:39:50.915 --> 02:39:53.126
No, sir. Lwill not.

02:39:59.841 --> 02:40:01.718
Very well. I withdraw it.

02:40:02.260 --> 02:40:03.970
Good for you, John.

02:40:08.641 --> 02:40:11.102
I'll speak to the printer
about it later on.

02:40:13.688 --> 02:40:15.481
Very well, gentlemen.

02:40:16.024 --> 02:40:19.861
We're about to brave the storm
in a skiff made of paper.

02:40:21.070 --> 02:40:23.072
And how it shall end,

02:40:23.156 --> 02:40:24.699
god only knows.

02:40:26.701 --> 02:40:28.828
That's a pretty large signature, Johnny.

02:40:28.912 --> 02:40:31.998
So fat George in London
can read it without his glasses.

02:40:34.626 --> 02:40:38.963
All right, step right up, gentlemen.
Don't miss your chance to commit treason.

02:40:40.798 --> 02:40:44.844
Hancock is right.
This paper is our passport to the gallows.

02:40:44.928 --> 02:40:46.179
But there's no backing out now,

02:40:46.262 --> 02:40:47.489
for if we do not hang together,

02:40:47.513 --> 02:40:50.266
we shall most assuredly hang separately.

02:40:52.518 --> 02:40:55.063
In my case, hanging won't be so bad.

02:40:55.146 --> 02:40:58.274
One snap and it'll be all
over, just like that.

02:40:58.358 --> 02:40:59.776
But look at read there.

02:40:59.859 --> 02:41:02.904
He'll be dancing a jig long after I'm gone!

02:41:04.864 --> 02:41:07.992
Gentlemen, forgive me
if I don't join in the merriment,

02:41:08.076 --> 02:41:10.036
but if we are arrested now,

02:41:10.161 --> 02:41:13.248
my name is still the only one
on the damn thing!

02:41:33.726 --> 02:41:37.063
"From the commander,
army of the united colonies in..."

02:41:38.273 --> 02:41:42.151
Army of the United States in New York,

02:41:42.235 --> 02:41:44.237
"dispatch number 1,209,

02:41:44.320 --> 02:41:46.048
"to the honorable congress,
John hancock, president.

02:41:46.072 --> 02:41:49.534
"Dear sir, I can now report
with some certainty

02:41:49.617 --> 02:41:51.577
"that the Eve of battle is near at hand.

02:41:52.412 --> 02:41:56.624
"Toward this end,
i have ordered the evacuation of Manhattan

02:41:56.708 --> 02:41:58.376
"and directed our defenses to take up

02:41:58.459 --> 02:42:00.962
"stronger positions on
the Brooklyn heights.

02:42:01.754 --> 02:42:03.840
"At the present time, my forces consist

02:42:03.923 --> 02:42:06.509
"entirely of haslet's Delaware militia

02:42:06.592 --> 02:42:08.469
"and smallwood's marylanders,

02:42:08.553 --> 02:42:12.265
"a total of 5,000 troops to stand against

02:42:14.642 --> 02:42:17.145
"twenty-five thousand of the enemy.

02:42:17.645 --> 02:42:19.814
"And I begin to notice that many of us

02:42:19.897 --> 02:42:24.027
"are lads under 15 and old men,

02:42:24.110 --> 02:42:27.071
"none of whom
could truly be called soldiers.

02:42:28.823 --> 02:42:31.117
"One personal note
to Mr. Lewis Morris of New York.

02:42:32.285 --> 02:42:33.661
"L must regretfully report

02:42:33.745 --> 02:42:36.831
"that his estates have
been totally destroyed,

02:42:36.914 --> 02:42:40.043
"but that I have taken
the Liberty of transporting Mrs. Morris

02:42:40.126 --> 02:42:43.463
"and eight of the children
to Connecticut and safety.

02:42:43.838 --> 02:42:48.051
"The four older boys
are now enlisted in the continental army.

02:42:48.968 --> 02:42:51.137
"As I write these words,

02:42:51.220 --> 02:42:54.307
"the enemy is plainly in sight
beyond the river.

02:42:55.683 --> 02:42:58.770
"How it will end, only
Providence can direct."

02:42:59.896 --> 02:43:02.148
"But, dear god, what brave men

02:43:06.319 --> 02:43:07.820
"lshafllose

02:43:10.365 --> 02:43:11.574
"before

02:43:12.700 --> 02:43:14.202
"this business

02:43:16.746 --> 02:43:17.914
"ends.

02:43:21.834 --> 02:43:23.628
"Your obedient,

02:43:27.173 --> 02:43:29.217
"g. Washington."

02:43:54.200 --> 02:43:55.993
Very well, gentlemen.

02:43:57.370 --> 02:43:58.579
Mcnair.

02:44:02.750 --> 02:44:04.377
Go ring the bell.

02:44:11.634 --> 02:44:12.677
Mr. president.

02:44:12.969 --> 02:44:14.345
Mr. Morris.

02:44:15.054 --> 02:44:16.806
To hell with New York.

02:44:16.889 --> 02:44:19.016
I'll sign it anyway.

02:44:19.100 --> 02:44:20.977
Thank you, Mr. Morris.

02:44:27.692 --> 02:44:29.902
Stephen, sit down.

02:44:31.070 --> 02:44:32.488
No.

02:44:32.572 --> 02:44:35.616
I want to remember
each man's face as he signs.

02:44:38.035 --> 02:44:39.370
Very well.

02:44:40.955 --> 02:44:42.331
Mr. thomson.

02:44:45.710 --> 02:44:48.921
New Hampshire. Dr. Josiah bartlett.

02:44:59.140 --> 02:45:00.391
Massachusetts.

02:45:00.933 --> 02:45:02.435
Mr. John Adams.

02:45:22.455 --> 02:45:25.041
Rhode Island. Mr. Stephen Hopkins.

02:45:32.632 --> 02:45:34.967
Connecticut. Mr. Roger sherman.

02:45:41.933 --> 02:45:44.602
New York. Mr. Lewis Morris.

02:45:51.734 --> 02:45:54.529
New Jersey.
The reverend John Witherspoon.

02:46:01.661 --> 02:46:05.164
Pennsylvania. Dr. Benjamin Franklin.

02:46:11.337 --> 02:46:14.131
Delaware. Mr. Caesar Rodney.

02:46:25.184 --> 02:46:27.353
Maryland. Mr. Samuel chase.

02:46:38.781 --> 02:46:41.367
Virginia. Mr. Thomas Jefferson.

02:46:48.874 --> 02:46:51.627
North Carolina. Mr. Joseph Hewes.

02:46:57.550 --> 02:47:00.094
South Carolina. Mr. Edward Rutledge.

02:47:06.434 --> 02:47:09.395
Georgia. Dr. lyman hall.
